title: spicy oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine flour, soda and salt and set aside.
Beat butter and shortening with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy. Add milk, egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and beat well.
Add oats, raisins and nuts and mix well. Drop teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on a wire rack.
Makes 30 to 36.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and cut center out of mushrooms. Fry bacon crisp and crumble into cream cheese.
Fill mushrooms with cream cheese and bacon mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425° or until mushrooms are slightly brown and bubbly.

title: blt egg bake
directions: Spread mayonnaise on one side of each slice of toast and cut into small pieces. Arrange toast, mayonnaise side up, in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Top with cheese slices and bacon. In a skillet, fry eggs over medium heat until completely set. Place over bacon. Top with tomato slices; set aside.

title: party cookies (m&m's)
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's (reserve remaining candies for decorating).
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and sour cream, mixing well.
Combine next 5 ingredients and add to batter; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Put beans in large bowl.
Brown in skillet the hamburger seasoned with salt, pepper, garlic and chopped peppers and chopped onions; drain grease off.
Add to beans.
Pour in tomato soup and mustard.
Stir and put in big baking dish.
You can use whatever amount of beans you need.
Bake at 350° until desired doneness.

title: aunt perk's sweet potato casserole
directions: Add ingredients together and put into baking dish.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Add broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon to a bowl. Mix mayo, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice. Pour over mixture in bowl.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheeses. Simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles until tender.
Layer 3 noodles and half of the hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle with half of each cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Roll in sesame seed. Eat!!

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool until barely warm.
Shake in a bag of confectioners sugar.

title: salmon pate
directions: Mix all ingredients into a food processor and mix until smooth.
Refrigerate for several hours. Serve on crackers, pita bread, or raw vegetables.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls over pizza pan, making crust.
Brown sausage and spread over crust.
Add hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over pizza.

title: canned grape juice
directions: Fill with hot water to neck of jar.
Cold pack for 35 minutes. This is a mild juice.

title: quick microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all of the ingredients (except margarine) in a glass bowl. Place the margarine on top of the mixture.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Press into a small baking dish. Refrigerate until cold and firm.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar slowly.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in sour cream.
Grease angel food cake pan.
Place 1/3 of Streusel on bottom of pan, then 1/2 of dough, 1/3 of Streusel and rest of dough.
Sprinkle remaining Streusel on top.
Bake in 350° oven 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare cornbread mix (with eggs and milk); add celery and onion.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Crumble cooked cornbread mix in large bowl.
Add reserved broth, salt, pepper, bread and seasoning.
Stir in chopped egg.
Spoon half of mix into greased shallow dish, spreading evenly.
Arrange chicken pieces on top. Spread on remaining dressing.
Top with soup and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber gel
directions: Use sugar-free gelatin, lite cottage cheese and low-fat mayonnaise to reduce calorie count.
In a shallow 10-inch baking dish, combine gelatin with water, stirring until completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended. Chill until firm and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: Saute squash and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in corn, salt, pepper, garlic and paprika; mix well.
Spoon mixture into casserole dish.
Top with croutons or bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: elizabeth's cookies
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Add water, vanilla, eggs, soft flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.
Cool further on wire rack.

title: gram's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugars.
Add
eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Mix well. Add oatmeal and mix.
Add nuts and chips.
Mix well.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: Put sugar and cornstarch in large shallow pan.
Stir, mixing well.
Add vinegar, cloves, ketchup, oil, salt and vanilla.
Stir again well.
Add beet juice from can.
Cut beets into bite size and put into pan.
Cook over medium fire 3 minutes, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Melt butter in oven in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or in microwave if using a microsafe baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter and lightly blend into butter. Arrange pineapple halves, cherries and pecans over sugar mixture.

title: hot pepperoni cheese dip
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring until cream cheese is melted.
Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Serve warm with vegetables and/or bread sticks.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: janice's peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixer bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water; mix well.
Add pudding mix and beat until blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Stir in extract; fold in whipped cream.
Pour half the cream mixture over cake slices; arrange half the peach slices on top.
Repeat layers, ending with some peach slices for garnish.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Cut into squares to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry yogurt cool whip pie(yields 8 servings)
directions: Dice up desired amount of strawberries into bite-size pieces. Leave some strawberries; cut in half for garnish.
Mix yogurt and Cool Whip on low speed with electric beater until light and fluffy.
Stir in diced strawberries.
Pour mixture into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours.
Garnish with remaining strawberries when ready to serve.
A great summer dessert!!

title: 7-up salad
directions: Pour 7-Up in pan and boil.
Pour over jello and cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool until jello begins to thicken.
Fold in pineapple, Dream Whip and nuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bread (and cookie) pudding
directions: Beat eggs gently (don't overbeat).
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla; blend.
Add cubed bread, cookies or cake; stir. Place saucer on pudding for few minutes so dry ingredients don't float and soak up liquid.
Cook in top of double boiler with water barely simmering; cook until table knife stuck in center comes out clean.
Serve with scoop of ice cream for each serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients.
Combine all and form small balls. Crisscross tops with fork on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked breakfast
directions: Preheat to 350°.
Brown sausage (or fry bacon and crumble). Drain.
Cool.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, mustard and cubed bread.
Stir.
Fold in cheese and meat.
Pour in greased 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight before baking.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin upside down cake
directions: Combine and place in a greased 9x13-inch pan.
Over the top sprinkle 1 box of yellow cake mix.
Drizzle over that, one cube of melted butter and the chopped pecans.
Gently press the pecans into the mixture.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and spoon over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate; set aside to cool.
Cream margarine.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add 3 eggs, beating well after each.
Stir melted chocolate into margarine mixture.
Add flour, salt, pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make 3 hamburger patties.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes, carrots and onions.
Tear off 3 big pieces of foil.
In the center of each piece, put a hamburger patty, potatoes, carrots, onions, salt and pepper.
Bring 4 corners of foil up and fold edges.
Will resemble a Hershey's Kiss.
Put on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 3.

title: mexicali baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gramma's molded salad
directions: Bring Jell-O, water and soup to a boil and set aside to cool. Stir rest of ingredients into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into mold or in flat cake pan.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add rice and slightly brown.
Mix the soup. Cook in buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix oleo, nuts and flour together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooked, cooled crust.
Mix 2 packages of pudding and 4 cups cold milk.
Spread this layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze until served.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 8 minutes.
Make sauce using cheese, butter, milk, salt and pepper.
In baking dish, place a layer of crackers, a layer of broccoli and then pour some sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: orange frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ice, in electric blender. Process until smooth.
Add ice; process until frothy.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as per package directions.
Spoon over nuts and coconut.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl until smooth.
Spoon evenly over cake, leaving 1-inch edge.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cream cheese mixture will sink to bottom to form frosting.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Mix in flavorings.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat until blended. Fold in pecans and fruits.
Turn into a 10-inch tube pan lined with greased waxed paper.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool.
Keep refrigerated or can be frozen.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Divide in 4 balls, roll each into roll and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Puncture foil so fat can drip out.
Slice thin and serve on crackers or sandwiches.

title: tom's favorite italian salad
directions: Marinate first 4 ingredients at least 2 hours.
Add to desired amounts of lettuce and fresh spinach just before serving.

title: tender tri-tip
directions: Follow directions on package of meat marinade except replace water with 4 ounces wine; increase oil amount to 4 ounces.
Add wine vinegar and minced garlic.

title: green potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes and make shallow slits around the middle as if you were cutting them in half lengthwise. Bake until done 45 to 60 minutes, depending on size.

title: easy baked ginger grouper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put fish in flat casserole dish. Saute onion and green pepper; add tomatoes, ginger and spices; boil.
Spoon over fish.
Bake 30 minutes or until just done. Don't overcook.
Serve with rice.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425° F (220° C).
Combine all ingredients except chicken in a small bowl.
Blend well.
Dip chicken pieces in batter and place on a baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown and tender.
Or, if desired, dip chicken pieces in batter then fry in hot oil.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: Dissolve 1 package
jello in 1 cup boiling water; add frozen strawberries and stir until berries separate and gelatin is slightly thickened.
Pour into a 5-cup mold; chill until set but not firm.
Meanwhile, dissolve 1 strawberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls; stir until ice cream melts.
Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.

title: ham and cheese spread
directions: Allow cheese to soften.
Mix cheese, onions and ham thoroughly.
Enjoy.

title: alda's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Add butter and mix well.
Pour into pie crust and top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes or until set.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in sugar. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: oven baked kalua pork
directions: Completely
thaw
pork	butt.
Preheat	oven
to
375°. Slice pork
butt in four sections about halfway through, then rub
down with
salt	and liquid smoke.
Wrap with a piece of banana leaf, then in ti-leaves.	Wrap tightly with foil; place in
a
baking pan.
Bake for 2 hours, then lower heat to 350° and
bake
another 2	hours.	Delicious
by
itself
or
with cabbage!

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, then add eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut. Drop onto ungreased
cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool for 2 minutes before transferring to wire rack.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Yield:
2 loaves.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to package; drain.
In large skillet, brown meat and stir in tomatoes and salt.
Heat through.
Combine with noodles; put into a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice in baking dish. Cover with bread. Mix sugar, butter and eggs and pour over peaches and bread. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pull-apart bacon bread
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon over medium heat for 5 minutes or until partially cooked; drain on paper towels. Roll out dough to 1/2 inch thickness; brush with 1 Tbsp. oil. cut into 1 inch pieces; place in a large bowl. Add the bacon, cheese, dressing mix and remaining oil; toss to coat. Arrange pieces in a 9
X 5 inch oval on a greased baking sheet, layering as needed. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes. Cover with foil; bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: quick fruit crumb
directions: Place peaches with juice in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking powder with fork.
Add beaten egg.
Spread over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: carrots in onion sauce
directions: To hot, drained spinach, add Tabasco, salt, butter and cream cheese that has been softened with milk.
Stir until butter has melted and ingredients are blended.

title: super salad seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix until evenly distributed.
Put in a 1-quart airtight container.
Label and store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 3 to 4 months.
Makes about 3 cups Super Salad Seasoning Mix.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and oil until moist. Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 2 cups bananas and walnuts.
Spoon batter into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pans to cooling rack to finish cooling.
Frost when completely cool.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour melted butter into bowl with all other ingredients and mix.
Pour back into casserole dish; bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cole slaw
directions: Blend together Miracle Whip, sugar and oil together well. Pour over slaw mixture and mix until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour and then stir again before serving.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Broil drumettes 20-25 minutes. Combine margarine, hot sauce & vinegar in saucepan. Heat until melted and blended.
Add chicken. Toss to coat evenly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 the noodles on bottom of casserole.
Layer chicken, mushrooms, onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in hot fat; add meat and seasonings until brown. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole, drained beans and soup.
Mash the potatoes; add milk, egg and seasonings.
Layer beans, layer soup, then layer mashed potatoes.
Meat goes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: This cake keeps well and is very moist.

title: prospector's sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cover and allow to stand at room temperature for 36 to 48 hours.

title: ruth bruce's apricot ribs
directions: Place ribs in a large heavy pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer gently until tender.
Place in pan and baste with sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, basting frequently.

title: peanut butter-chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in water and egg.
Mix in flour, soda and salt. Stir in peanuts and candies.
Spread dough in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on round pizza pan.
Bake until done, slightly brown.
Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar, then blend in Cool Whip.
Put fruit in a ring around on top until you get to center.
Chill one hour.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute onion in shortening; add seasonings and chicken and saute about 10 minutes. Add water, cover and simmer slowly until chicken is tender.*
Add sour cream to pan and mix well. Heat through and serve with mashed potatoes or dumplings. Serves 4.

title: too good noodles and eggs
directions: Do not overcook noodles.
Use bacon drippings; fry noodles and saute onions.
Add tomato pieces.
Scramble eggs.
Add to noodle and onion mixture.
You may add frozen peas.

title: coconut chinese chews
directions: Mix ingredients in order named.
Spread it thin on a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° until done, not allowing the edges to become hard.
Cut into 1-inch squares and roll between your palms into ball shapes. When cool, ice each and roll thickly in shredded coconut.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and wash all the beans and the corn.
Finely chop the peppers, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add the sugar, vinegar and dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: crazy caramel rolls
directions: Combine water, butter and sugar.
Cook until butter melts and mixes with other ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Stir and coat each quarter in mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except spaghetti. Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar; add zucchini, oil and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt into wet ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine chiles, sour cream and salt. Spread 1 cup cooked rice in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with a layer of 1/3 of the sour cream mixture, then 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over sugar, flour and marshmallows in bowl; stir until marshmallows melt.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Spread Coca-Cola Frosting over top of cake.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Combine milk, chuck, crackers, onion, salt and cheese in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Cut hamburger buns in half.
Toast lightly.
Spread meat mixture evenly over top of each bun.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl and pour into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; crumble and set aside.
Separate dinner rolls and arrange in oblong pan; press sides together to form crust. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Crust will be puffy.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheese.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pie mix, eggs, sugar and milk; pour into cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Pour melted butter over cake mix; top with pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Cake:
Sift together the sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the shortening, oleo, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture while hot.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in sheet pan in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in walnuts.
Shape dough into rolls.
Place on waxed paper.
Roll up.
Place in refrigerator and chill completely.
Cut dough in rounds.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice the tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Do not peel or core. Drain well between paper toweling until most of the moisture of the tomatoes is absorbed.
Beat the eggs until light.
Mix in cornmeal, water, chives, salt and pepper.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 c. hot water.
When cool add strawberries, which have been thawed, and lemon juice.
Whip cream and add to mixture.
Put a layer of mixture in bottom of pan. Break cake into small chunks.
Alternate layers of cake and mixture until all is used.
Chill.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Prepare puddings according to package directions.
Line graham crackers on bottom and sides of square pan.
Pour vanilla pudding on graham crackers and smooth out, put another layer of graham crackers and top this with the chocolate pudding then top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.
Enjoy!

title: eva's tomato aspic
directions: Season tomato juice to	your
liking
with
seasonings. Melt gelatin in small amount of tomato juice over medium heat. Mix with remainder of juices
and
grated
onion.
When
this mixture begins to congeal, add
sliced
or	chopped olives and celery. Slice in squares when
congealed.
I add more gelatin (about 2 teaspoons).
It slices
or	unmolds better.
Yield: 2 Pyrex dishes, 10 x 6-inches.

title: butter crescents
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl. Add 1 cup melted butter, sugar, eggs and salt; stir well.
Gradually add flour, mixing well. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 4 hours.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Place rhubarb in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with the gelatin, sugar and marshmallows. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter over marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes. Invert cake onto a serving platter. Serve with whipped topping, if desired. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place sweet potatoes in large mixer bowl and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except egg whites; blend until smooth.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl with clean beaters at medium speed until stiff but not dry.
Fold into potato mixture.
Pour into 8-inch nonstick baking pan and bake uncovered 50 to 60 minutes until golden and set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broiled lamb
directions: Combine all ingredients except for lamb.
Mix well and pour over lamb in glass dish.
Turn lamb to coat well.
Refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.

title: spicy taco dip
directions: Combine Ranch dressing, mayo, milk and sour cream.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheeses, peppers, black olives and tomatoes.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar, egg, butter and vanilla in skillet.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll in coconut.
Makes about 56 balls.

title: pepper steak
directions: Soak strips of steak in soy sauce at least 30 minutes.
Cut up medium onion and large bell pepper in chunks.
Heat margarine until it sizzles, then cook onions and peppers until they are tender.
Drain steak; add to vegetables and cook for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add small amount of soy sauce to taste along with salt and pepper.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Put milk, shortening and sugar in saucepan over low heat; let scald, not boil.
Take off heat and when lukewarm, add yeast which has been dissolved in small amount of water.
Place mixture in a large bowl and add enough flour to make dough the consistency of waffle batter.
Let rise for two hours until doubled in bulk.
Add salt, baking powder and soda and enough flour to make dough.
Take half of mixture and place in another bowl.
Cover each bowl with foil and place in refrigerator and let rise overnight.
Dough will keep for a week to 10 days in refrigerator and full recipe does not have to baked at one time.
Take amount of desired dough from bowl. Place on floured board and make rolls into desired shape.
Place on greased pan and let rise for 2 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Yields approximately 75 rolls.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together until creamy.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix baking powder, soda, salt and flour together.
Add these alternately with buttermilk and bananas into sugar mixture. Add vanilla and pecans.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and egg and beat.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well and let stand for 2 hours. Then work down well and make into small balls.
Let rise for 2 hours and then bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan. Fry potatoes in bacon grease along with onions and peppers. Dice bacon and add to
mixture. Season.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: You will need a measuring cup, 30 cm (12-inch) deep, rectangular dish, wooden spoon and kitchen knife.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all except for cheese.
Put into casserole dish; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: In large bowl beat shortening until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars.
Beat well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine oats, flour, salt and soda; stir well.
Stir in vanilla; add chocolate chunks and pecans.
This will be very stiff.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool, then transfer to wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and boil one minute.
Cool and pour over the remainder of ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, spices and sugar together in a large bowl. Add applesauce, melted butter, raisins and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Best to bake the day before it is served.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Beat cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar together.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and milk.
Stir well.
Add American cheese spread; heat and stir until mixture is smooth. Add broccoli and rice.
Mix well.
Place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave enchilada casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and garlic in 2-quart casserole. Microwave at High 5 to 9 minutes.
Break up beef and drain.
Stir in sauce, water, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring after 1/2 time.
Alternately layer tortillas, meat sauce and cheese in 1 1/2-quart round casserole, ending with cheese.
Microwave at High 1 to 3 minutes until cheese is melted. Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: my best meat loaf
directions: Melt Spry in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Fry about 10 minutes.
Combine all remaining ingredients except catsup.
Add onion and mix thoroughly.
Pack in 5 x 10-inch Spry coated loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 1 hour. Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan; cook until thick.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in
a small amount of grease in frying pan. Set aside.
Spray
baking dish with Pam.
Layer potatoes in bottom of pan.
Arrange
pork
chops
on
top
of potatoes. Pour cream of mushroom or cream of chicken soup on top of pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: zucchini-sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage.
Break up very small.
Stir together all ingredients except zucchini.
Add that last.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm. They warm up in oven covered, very nicely.

title: coconut chew's
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in flour.
Press evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread over hot baked layer.
Bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: lima and ham salad
directions: Combine dressing, beans, potatoes, ham, celery, green onion, parsley and chives in a large salad bowl.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Before serving, stir in snow peas or sugar snap peas.
To serve, if desired, place halved tomato slices on a platter.
Top the salad mixture, or mound portions of salad on individual lettuce lined plates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Beat eggs, then add cake mix, cherry pie mix and almond flavoring, mixing by hand.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan (11 x 16-inch) and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients in plastic baggie.
Mix egg and milk.
Dip chicken in egg and milk, then place in baggie; shake well.
Place in pan.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: sunrise pound cake
directions: Beat eggs seven minutes.
Continue slowly beating and slowly pour in cup of cooking oil.
Slowly pour in two cups of sugar. When this is well blended, slowly add the two cups of sifted flour.
Beat seven more minutes.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for at least an hour.
This makes a large cake.

title: potato hamburger casserole
directions: Butter baking dish.
Slice potatoes to cover bottom of dish. Slice onion and lay across potatoes.
Cook Minute rice and spread on top of onion.
Cook hamburger; drain and put on top.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover hamburger with vegetable soup right out of can. Pour 1 to 1 1/2 cans water (use soup can) over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: german meatball and noodle casserole
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion, milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
In a medium skillet (medium-low heat) in hot salad oil, brown meatballs; add undiluted beef broth and simmer, covered 30 minutes.
In a large saucepan, cook noodles and drain.
Toss caraway seed and noodles.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the peanut butter, powdered sugar, butter, vanilla and mayonnaise.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape mix into balls.
Stick toothpick in and dip into melted chocolate and paraffin, 3/4 of way.
(Melt the chocolate in double boiler.)
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix well the butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Sift together and stir in flour and salt. Stir in nuts. Chill dough. Heat oven to 400°.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until set but not brown. While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Let cool, then roll again in sugar.

title: holiday snowflakes
directions: Melt candy according to package instructions.
In a large mixing bowl add Chinese noodles and peanuts to candy mixture and stir well until all covered with chocolate mixture.
Place onto wax paper with a teaspoon to form mounds.
Sprinkle mounds with green and red crystals and let cool.

title: porcupine beef balls
directions: Lightly grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Set aside sauce.
Add 1/2 cup water if sauce is thick.
Combine beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and put in casserole. Pour tomato sauce over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with eggs and flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato "stuff"
directions: Cut up tomatoes, onion and peppers; cook until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend the flour and water together; add to cooked mixture.
This will slightly thicken the mixture.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Drain liquid from fruit cocktail and save.
Add crushed pineapple, drained mandarin oranges and marshmallows.
Rinse maraschino cherries and add.
These can also be cut in half.
Add Cool Whip to make it soft.
Refrigerate.
Add remaining fruit juice as mixture thickens.

title: milk chocolate and peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Spread evenly over top.
Makes 48 bars.

title: jean's broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water, onion and margarine to a boil.
Add broccoli; stir until thawed.
Remove from heat; add rice.
Cover and let stand five minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup.
Put in a 2-quart casserole; top with onion rings.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: steak and rice special
directions: Flour and brown steak in oil, turning to brown all sides.
Add onion and stir constantly until transparent.
Add water and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Thaw out strawberries.
Mix in pie filling.
Add bananas; stir.
Chill well and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine, potatoes, sour cream, undiluted chicken soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Divide into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Cover each with topping of crushed corn flakes and other stick of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
You may freeze one for later use if desired.
Very good piping hot!!

title: rhubarb dream dessert
directions: Blend together and press mixture into ungreased 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and 1 stick margarine, add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, beat well.
Add combined flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in 1 tsp. vanilla and 1 c. pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into three greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: felix's chicken breasts
directions: Line baking dish with dried beef. Wrap chicken breasts with bacon strips and place in the baking dish. Mix mushroom soup and mushrooms with sour cream; spread over the chicken. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cinnamon loaf(breakfast)
directions: You will need two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to instructions.
Add oleo.
Mix well. Add corn and soup.
Add cheese; combine with mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle some cheese on top; sprinkle some paprika on top for color (optional).
Put back in oven until cheese melts.
Very good.

title: play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar in a heavy saucepan. Stir in water and oil.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for about 3 minutes, or until mixture thickens and turns loose from sides of pan.
Remove from heat and add desired food coloring.
Let cool and dough will remain soft and pliable in an airtight container.

title: chocolate coconut cruncher cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and eggs and mix well.
Add coconut, pecans, cornflakes, rolled oats and chocolate chips and mix well.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Spread caramel dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Pour milk in a large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and Heath bars.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until set.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: rum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour into well-buttered tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Keep warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cheese needs to be at room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet pickled banana peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Remove seeds and soak in ice water for 3 hours, then drain.
Make a syrup of the ingredients listed and bring to a boil.
Pour boiling syrup over peppers that have been packed into clean sterilized jars.
Seal at once.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix all together (batter will be stiff).
Using your fingers, pat into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese fruit dip
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and orange juice until smooth.
Fold in marshmallow cream and serve with your favorite fruits.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in stick of butter, add sour cream, mushroom soup and cheese, mix until cheese starts to melt.
In a 13 x 9 x 2 greased dish pour frozen tater tots.
Pour cheese mixture over top. Place in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes. 5 minutes before cooking time is complete sprinkle with bacon bits, garlic salt and parsley flakes

title: sweet refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Melt margarine in remaining warm water.
Add sugar, salt and beaten egg to margarine and water.
Cook to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 1/2 of flour; mix until all ingredients are well blended.
Add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn once to grease top of dough.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to use, take out needed amount.
Make into rolls.
Place in lightly greased pans and let rise 3 to 4 hours, until double in size. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Total amount will yield 48 rolls.

title: chicken extra special
directions: Chicken:
Fry chicken cutlets in a small amount of oil by first dipping in eggs and bread crumbs.
Drain on paper towels.
Set aside.

title: oven baked caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, syrup, oleo and cream of tartar to a slow boil.
Stir to keep from burning.
Remove from heat and add soda and salt; stir well.
Pour over popped corn and stir until well coated.
Keep warm while stirring.
Spread on cookie sheet or a deep roaster.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Cool. May be put in plastic bags and frozen.
Eat directly from freezer.

title: catfish in beer batter
directions: Let
beer stand open for 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients, folding in egg whites last.
Coat fillets and fry.
Very light batter.

title: capital chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chicken on all sides in oil and butter.
Remove chicken and place in a long casserole.
Saute mushrooms in the oil and butter.
Stir in flour.
Add cream of chicken soup, sherry and broth.
Simmer about 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in half and half, salt, tarragon leaves and pepper.
Pour sauce over the chicken.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour. Add artichoke hearts, green onions and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Serve with wild rice.

title: okra and shrimp pilaus
directions: Wash okra and cut into slices, taking off tops and bottoms. In a deep saucepan, cook bacon and remove after it is crisp.
Add onion, shrimp and okra, cooking until tender (do not burn).
Add salt and pepper, making sure that it is to your taste.
Wash rice and put in saucepan along with other ingredients.
Add just enough water to cover.
Cook at high speed until water starts to boil. Reduce heat to a medium-low heat and stir frequently.
Keep a tight lid on when not stirring.
Cook until rice is fluffy.
Serve with chicken, beef and pork roasts.

title: pacific tamato basil pasta salad
directions: Rinse capers under cold running water and pat dry with paper towels.
Place in large salad bowl with the tomatoes, green onion, garlic and basil.
Combine lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add oil and stir until blended.
Fill large pan with salted water and bring to boil.
Add pasta and boil until cooked but still firm.
Drain and rinse under cold running water.
Add to salad bowl.
Pour the dressing over salad.
Toss well.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: meatballs (3)
directions: Mix above together & make into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, 1 stick margarine/butter, sour cream, cheese and onion. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add topping and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mother's sweet pickle recipe(pearl bassett)
directions: Mix lime and water; add sliced cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours. Next day, pour water and lime off cucumbers.
Let cucumbers set in ice cold water for 4 hours.
Important: Change water every hour!
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt together; put cucumbers in solution.
Leave overnight.
Cook next a.m.
Starting on high heat, bring to a boil; cut stove down to medium heat and boil for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Brown steak well on both sides.
Place in casserole for baking. Put a slice of onion on top of each piece of steak.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over steak pieces.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat orange angel food cake
directions: Slice angel food cake in half.
Prepare jello as directed. While jello is warm, pour jello over cake bottom half, then add top and pour remaining jello over cake.
Chill.
Ice with Cool Whip and add oranges to top of cake just before serving.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Place cooked chicken (broiled or boiled) in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Mix butter, poppy seed and crushed crackers together and spread over top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta cheese and salsa in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High for 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve as directed.

title: pinto bean salad
directions: Drain pinto beans. Lightly toss all ingredients together. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot grease until limp.
Drain on paper towels.

Combine 2 cans soup, 1 package of cheese, 1/2 pint of sour cream, comino, garlic salt, 1 can chilies and diced chicken. Place 1 large tablespoon of mixture on each tortilla and roll. Place each enchilada tightly against next in long baking dish. Mix second package of cheese, soups (undiluted), remaining sour cream and chilies in bowl.
Stir well and spread over enchiladas. Place in 325° oven and heat until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: supper vegetables au gratin
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over high heat, heat water, cauliflower and frozen green beans to boiling. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until tender. Remove vegetables; discard water.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut meat into very thin strips.
Soak for 12 hours in mixture. Put in cookie sheet and cook in oven on low heat (160°) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken ala orange with rice
directions: Cook chicken with salt and pepper until done.
Cut into strips.
Brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons of margarine or butter.
Remove from skillet.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Place chicken in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.
Also good cooked on grill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Form into a ball; roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper, seasoning and 2 cups cheese.
Mix together. Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 5 minutes longer at 300°.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, milk, salt, pepper, butter and cheese, then add potatoes.
Pour in large baking dish.
Bake 1 hour covered.
Stir and bake 1/2 hour uncovered at 375°.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 5 well beaten eggs.
Sift spices, baking powder, cocoa and flour; add alternately with soda-buttermilk mixture to the other ingredients.
Add nuts, raisins, preserves and vanilla to batter.
Bake at 375°.
This makes either a four layer cake, or divide and make two cakes according to size of pans.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cut the onion paper thin.
Slice cooked potatoes.
Layer ingredients in order, then repeat.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Sauce:
Combine 1 can tomato paste, melted oleo and 1/2 teaspoon of Italian seasoning.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook a hen or thighs and legs.
Bake cornbread to make dressing.
Add celery and onions to broth after chicken is removed.
Add salt and pepper to taste; add margarine.
Crumble bread into broth.
Add eggs.
Add deboned chopped chicken.
If mixture is too dry, add milk; if too thin, add more cornbread. Pour into greased baking dish and bake until a light brown at 350°.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice them thin.
Set aside. Cut bacon in squares, dice medium onion and fry both together until bacon is crisp.
Remove bacon and drain on paper.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add peanut butter, eggs, oatmeal and sifted dry ingredients.
Add chips and nuts. Mix well. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Whisk the next 7 ingredients. Mix all together until moistened.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
While macaroni is cooking, brown ground meat and onion with salt to taste.
Add all ingredients in large pot or Dutch oven.
Cook on low until cheese is melted and all ingredients are blended, stirring often to prevent sticking. Serves 8.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Place apples and potatoes in baking dish.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake until light brown in 350° oven.

title: creamed crabmeat
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on toasted bun or English muffin.
Run under broiler until bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna log
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley.
Shape into log or ball.
Roll in parsley.
Chill.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain green beans, corn and peas.
Mix vegetables with onion, pimento and celery.
Heat sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over vegetables.
Best if refrigerated overnight.
Yields 10 servings. Preparation time is 15 minutes.

title: slender'rific dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with veggies or crackers.
This is low calorie.

title: daily bread stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan or pot.
Cook to boiling, then simmer until it seems done.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot on high for a few hours.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix and heat.
Use warm chafing dish to keep warm.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Follow all directions on chocolate cake box and pudding.
Make whipped cream.
Add confectioners sugar to heavy cream and beat until fluffy.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten croissants on cookie sheet.
Bake as directed.
Cool. Top with Ranch dressing.
Then top with veggies and cheese. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: western hash
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: time-to-spare ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Shake flour in oven cooking bag. Place in 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Cut ribs in serving pieces; place in bag.
Turn bag to coat ribs.
Arrange ribs in even layers.
Close bag with nylon tie, cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Blend flour, soda and salt.
Stir in.
Add nuts if you want to.
Chill dough if soft.
Drop by tablespoons on greased pan. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan and spray with cooking spray.
Drain salmon, saving liquid. Discard skin, but save bones.
Flake salmon lightly, but well with fork.
Crush bones (calcium bonus) and mix.
Add vinegar to salmon liquid and enough cold water to make 1/2 cup total liquid.
Add to salmon.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Leave loaf in pan for 5 minutes before unmolding onto serving plate.

title: jello surprise
directions: Pour uncooked jello into bowl.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple.
Mix in with jello and other ingredients.
Add walnuts.
Stir well (it will be thick).
Refrigerate and let chill for 1 hour.

title: mary may's pecan candy-cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour that has been sifted with salt and baking powder, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three (8 or 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 375°, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk crumb cake
directions: Mix with a spoon.
Do not beat.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside.
Reserve 3 tablespoons bacon drippings in saucepan; discard remainder.
Add onion slices to saucepan and cook until lightly browned.
Add diced potatoes and water; cook over medium heat until potato is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn, milk, salt and pepper; cook until heated through.
Pour into warmed bowl; top each serving with crumbled bacon and a pat of butter or margarine.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Pour oil into mixing bowl and add sugar.
Beat until blended. Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating until thick and smooth. Blend together red food coloring, cocoa and vinegar.
Beat well. Add vanilla and blend.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and sprinkle onto apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or enjoy it all by itself. A quick and easy dessert all will love!

title: danish squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13 cake pan.
Unroll one tube of crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Pinch seams together.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread mixture on top of crescent rolls.
Unroll other tube of crescent rolls and place on top of cheese mixture.
Beat egg white until foamy and spread on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon & sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine the egg yolks and condensed milk and last, add the lime juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with either meringue or whipped cream.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Mash bananas and eggs.
Mix in half and half, sugar and milk. Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and milk and heat.
Beat egg yolks.
Add flour combined with sugar and salt.
Pour into hot mixture and cook until it begins to thicken.
Add lemon juice and grated rind and cook 1 minute; stir.
Add butter; stir well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat 2 egg whites combined with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Add 4 teaspoons of sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Use 2 cups of drained fruit juice and mix with instant lemon pudding.
Let thicken a little.
Combine with completely drained fruit.
Add lemon juice and bananas before serving.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix like pie crust (no water).
Press into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in the bottom of greased casserole dish.
Spread chicken over broccoli, then add mixture of first 4 ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Dissolve yeast	in water.
Blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let
stand	until
bubbly.	Add
rest
of sugar, milk, salad oil and salt.
Put
on
low speed of mixer and add flour 1 cup at a time.
Beat
in
last
cup
with heavy spoon. Add flour until dough is heavy
and
stiff
but
too sticky to knead.
Place dough in
two
well-greased 1 pound coffee cans. Cover with well-greased plastic
can lids.
You may freeze the dough at this point.
It will keep for two weeks.
Let covered cans stand until dough pops	off
lids.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Crust
will
be	brown.	Brush lightly with butter. After
cooling
10	minutes, remove from can.

title: diet orange cake
directions: Grind orange and raisins together; set aside.
Cream Sweet 'N Low and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, buttermilk, soda and orange mixture.
Add oatmeal and flour; beat well.
Turn into 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: ellen's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with rice and set aside.
Over low flame, or in microwave,
melt together the soup and cheese. Pour over broccoli and rice mix.
Add water chestnuts and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and cover.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
(Can use microwave instead.)

title: olive garden sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients except for ice.
Pour Sangria in glass and then add ice.
Make sure there is fruit in every glass. Maraschino cherries can also be added.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until
almost tender.
Drain.
Put macaroni into a large baking dish.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well. Cook, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serves about 12.
Costs about 8 cents per serving.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix pumpkin seeds, salt and oil together and spread single layer on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, turning seeds every 10 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough; otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through. (Use handle of spoon to prevent knife from cutting through.) Place in microwave safe bowl and sprinkle with melted butter and herbs.
Microwave on high 10 minutes, rearranging after 5 minutes. Let rest 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and parmesan cheese.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes on high until cheese melts and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: hot dog roll-ups
directions: Place frankfurter in center of each slice bread.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, relish and mustard.
Spoon about 2 teaspoons mayonnaise mixture over frankfurter; secure with wooden picks. Place roll-ups, seam sides down, in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Brush with margarine.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven until hot and golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Yields 8 sandwiches.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, almonds, onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and crushed chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serves approximately 6.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Whip chilled milk until stiff peaks form.
Add lemon juice, jello and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into dish lined with crumbs. Sprinkle top with crumbs and chill before serving.

title: hot ham and cheese dip in bread
directions: Cut off top of round loaf of bread.
Scoop out pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into hollow of bread.
Put top on. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with scooped out pieces of bread.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers (optional), then slice thin; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl large enough to accommodate cucumbers.
Add cucumbers and mix well.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will stay nice for approximately 1 week.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine dry ingredients; add to mixture and mix well.
Bake in two well-greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger in casserole dish.
Cover with onion slices and then put your cheese over the onion.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over layers.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Do not salt.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sunny fruit salad
directions: Layer in casserole.
For last layer, pour cherry pie filling over top, then pour sherry over whole salad.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: caramel apple delight
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients, using electric mixer.
Use as dip for apple slices.
Tastes like caramel apples.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into ball(s).
Roll ball(s) into nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: roasted ratatouille
directions: Set oven racks at 2 lowest levels.
Heat oven to 450°.
Peel papery skin from garlic and wrap head in aluminum foil.
Bake 30 minutes; cool.
Meanwhile, coat 2 baking sheets with vegetable oil or nonstick spray and arrange tomatoes, eggplant, zucchini, squash, onions and peppers on baking sheets.
Roast 20 minutes, turning once, until tender and brown.
Cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in the corn.
In a large skillet heat the shortening or oil and drop batter by tablespoons into the very hot fat.
Fry until browned on both sides.

title: grape blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-o in boiling water. Add all other ingredients, stirring well. Congeal in 13 x 9
glass
dish.

title: apple pie
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over sliced apples.
Coat well and pour into pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings. Calories per serving 103.

title: pasta-sausage soup
directions: Remove casings from the sausages and cut into 1-inch pieces. In a Dutch oven, brown sausage over medium heat.
Remove sausage and drain all but 2 tablespoons of the drippings.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic until tender.
Add sausage and all remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until pasta is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: wonderful wheat waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine yolks, milk and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Fold in stiff egg whites, leaving it slightly fluffy (curdled looking).
Bake in waffle iron.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tuna balls
directions: Combine.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Bake in oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve with favorite sauce.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, well and chill.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Serve.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in oats (quick or regular oats) and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir halfway through baking.
Will be golden brown.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine margarine and sugar; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs and sour cream.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour half of the batter into prepared pan; spread with cherry pie filling, then pour remaining batter over pie filling.

title: yellow cookies
directions: Mix.
Roll into cookie size balls.
Roll in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Cook meat, onion, chili blend or chili powder, salt and pepper together until done.
Mix milk, soups and green chilies together. Start with tortillas or chips on bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan. Layer tortillas or chips, meat mixture on top, then soup mixture on top of meat.
Repeat layers until all is gone.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cook until hot through and through.

title: mound balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips and wax in double broiler.
May need teaspoon or so of milk.
Mix first 4 ingredients and make into balls.
Roll around in chocolate chips and wax.
Place on waxed paper and let cool.

title: black bean and salsa salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Blend the salsa with red vinegar dressing;
pour over salad and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Serves 8.

title: texas matador
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add tomatoes, onion and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Boil noodles 10 minutes and drain.
Add noodles and meat mixture with cream cheese, salt, pepper and sugar.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbled; drain excess fat. In crock-pot, melt cheeses.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Serve with favorite chips.
Makes a large amount and it can be frozen.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Cook dates in water a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Set aside and let cool.
When cool, add nuts.
Thoroughly cream sugar and oleo, add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients and mix.
Knead dough, divide in half, roll one part on floured board 1/4-inch thick in a rectangular shape.
Spread half of date mixture all over the dough and roll like a jelly roll, wrap in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Repeat with the remaining dough and filling.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Shred zucchini.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini, and vanilla. Mix flour, raisins, nuts and cinnamon.
Add to above.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: salad apple ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin and dash of salt in 2 cups hot water; cool to room temperature and add lemon juice.
Carefully pour lemon-lime beverage down side of bowl; stir gently with up and down motion. Chill until partially set.
Meanwhile, core apples and slice very thinly.
Add apples and grapes to gelatin mixture, stirring gently with up and down motion.
Pour into 2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Bake chops in oven approximately 15 minutes.
To mix barbecue sauce, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops and finish cooking another 15 minutes.

title: lubee (green beans)
directions: Brown onion and ground beef (you do not have to use oil).
Add tomato paste, spices, water and green beans.
Simmer for about 40 minutes.
May be served with rice.
Serves about 4.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions. Drain.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Melt together soup and cheese.
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower.
Mix together melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugar, butter and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift the dry ingredients in and blend well.
Chill the dough before shaping.
Roll 2 teaspoons of dough for each ball. Roll the balls in granulated sugar.
Put balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked vegetable omelet
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer Pepper Jack cheese, vegetables, then Cheddar cheese in dish.
Beat milk, flour, salt, pepper and eggs until smooth; pour over cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° until the egg mixture is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Great for brunch!!

title: janice's chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in large pot of water seasoned with Tony's seasoning, a little cayenne pepper and bouillon cubes.
When chicken is cooked, remove and debone.
Add chopped celery and carrots to broth; cook 15 minutes.
Then add chopped chicken and vermicelli.
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: baked soybeans
directions: Pressure cook soybeans in water 1 hour.
Drain juice from tomatoes and add to sauteed onions in heavy skillet.
Simmer.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces and add to juice.
Add brown sugar, oil and salt.
Mix.
Add to cooked soybeans.
(I often just add all these ingredients to beans without any precooking.)
Bake at 350° until juice is thickened.
Add lemon juice and sweet basil.
Add 1/2 can plain tomato paste.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven in an oblong baking dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook macaroni shells.
Put spaghetti sauce, garlic, onion, green pepper and oregano into saucepan and cook for 30 minutes. Add rest of ingredients (except cheeses) together.
Layer into casserole dish, layer of macaroni, layer of sauce and layer of cheese.
Repeat until all mixture is used up.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Serve immediately or chill several hours.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: "sitting pretty" cookies
directions: Sift together flour and salt; set aside.
Mix together the butter, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Add slowly to flour mixture. Roll into small balls; dip into egg white.
Roll into chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove and make thumbprint in center of each cookie.
Put back in oven for 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Let cool completely, then fill each hole with sour cream frosting.
Garnish by placing 1 peanut M&M in center of frosting.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
Just mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: wild plum tree muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into miniature muffin tins about 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Watch carefully!

title: banana cranberry jam
directions: Simmer cranberries and water for 10 minutes. Add mashed bananas and sugar; bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add pectin. Stir and skim. Put in sterile jars and seal.
Yield:
Eight 8-ounce jars.

title: cracker mix
directions: You will need 1 large Ziploc plastic bag.

title: jalapeno bloody marias
directions: In a blender put half of tomato juice and jalapeno chili. Process until chili is pureed.
Fill a cocktail shaker with ice and add tomato-jalapeno mixture and remaining ingredients.
Shake well and strain into highball glasses.

title: india chicken curry
directions: Simmer onion and celery in butter.
Add flour; mix thoroughly. Add chicken stock and cook until smooth.
Add tomato juice, seasonings and chicken.
Arrange rice in a ring and pour hot curried chicken in the center.

title: brittany stew
directions: Boil 1/2 package of egg noodles according to directions on bag.
On medium to low heat, warm beef stew in saucepan.
When noodles are ready, drain and place in bowl.
Add beef stew and serve.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Clean up mess.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Mix in blender and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with grated Hershey bars and pecans.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cheryle's golden punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in some of water; combine juice with remaining water.
Pour into punch bowl with ice cubes or ice ring.
Top with cold ginger ale.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to sugar mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until slightly golden in a 350° oven.
Frost with lemon icing.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix with rubber spatula.
Freeze or chill before serving.

title: aunt poly's sweet pickles
directions: Drain off and throw away all vinegar from the jug of dill pickles.
Cut pickles into wheels, do not cut too thin.
Return the pickles to gallon jug and add the sugar to pickles.
(It works best if you layer the pickles and sugar a couple times.)
Tighten the lid on jar and turn; shake the jar several times a day until all sugar has dissolved.
Add 1 ounce of Tabasco hot sauce and mix well.
You can do this by turning jug upside down several times. The pickles will be crisp in a week to 10 days.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons for each serving.
Makes 1 pound.

title: peanut blossoms(cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients except kisses in a large mixer bowl. Shape dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Take chicken off bones and put in bottom of flat 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine and spread over soup and chicken.
Do not stir.
Pour 2 cups of chicken broth on top; do not stir. Bake at 350° until done, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese bits
directions: Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and press down with fork.
Bake at 350° to 375° about 15 minutes.

title: cornmeal scrapple
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cornmeal, milk, sugar and salt; gradually stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat; cook, covered, 10 minutes longer or until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in sausage.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate. To serve, cut 1/3-inch slices; dip in flour on both sides.
Fry in skillet in melted butter over medium heat until browned on both sides.
Serve warm with syrup.

title: lemon butter shrimp with angel hair pasta
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add next 8 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: sunset dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9-inch microwave safe pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with salsa and serve with chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Excellent for parties.

title: country corn muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: asparagus and green pea casserole
directions: *Or toasted slivered almonds.
This is my preference.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together real well except margarine.
Put in baking dish and top with margarine.
Bake at 325° for at least an hour (onion needs to fully cook).
You can saute onion before adding and bake only about 1/2 the original time.

title: corn popovers
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonful into hot grease to deep fry.
Fry until golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, blend orange juice, sugar, milk, water and vanilla. Add ice cubes. Blend well. Serve immediately.

title: ricotta balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl, drop by spoonful in oil and deep fry.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Keep refrigerated, if any are left.

title: pecan-crunch sweet potato pie
directions: Blend together pecans, 1/3 cup brown sugar and butter.
Press gently onto bottom of pie shell. Mix and beat gently to blend remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 400° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain, chop and set aside.
Separate rolls and press into a 12-inch pizza pan to the center.
Spoon sausage on crust; top with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and spices; pour over sausage mixture.
Sprinkle half of Parmesan cheese over egg mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese; return to oven and bake 5 minutes.

title: basic streusel topping
directions: Combine
the
sugars
and
flour in a medium size bowl. Add the
margarine;
mix well.	Very good on baked apple pie, rather than a top crust.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix all together and chill for 2 hours.

title: olive-cream cheese bagels
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches 115°. Remove from heat; transfer to a large bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: easy chip dip
directions: Mix deviled ham and cream cheese.
Thin to desired consistency with milk.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, green pepper, onion and Italian seasoning.
Drain.
Add soup and pizza sauce.
Mix together.

title: glenn's chicken wings
directions: Put half of mixture in bowl and marinate overnight.
Drain wings when ready to cook.
Cook on grill, turning frequently. When almost done, put wings in bowl with rest of marinade to which 2 tablespoons of butter has been added.
Return wings to grill, turning once.

title: cucumber salad(very tasty!)
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; cool slightly.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill until set and serve.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Mixture will be bubbling all over the top.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat. Stir in chocolate pieces until completely melted.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spread on buttered pan.

title: french pastry pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, Crisco and sugar until it resembles corn meal.
In small bowl, put egg, water and vinegar.
Mix well with fork.
Add to flour mixture and mix until well blended, then roll out for crusts.
Makes 4 single crusts or 2 double crust pies. Freezes well.

title: venison stew
directions: Saute venison cubes in small amount of oil until brown.
Add celery, pepper, carrots, onion and shallots.
Take some of drippings from pan and make a roux with the flour (cook until brown like for gravy).
Add this to the pot, then add enough water to cover.
Cook about 3 hours or until tender.
