title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken over rice.
Pour onion soup mix over chicken.
Add cream of chicken mushroom soup.
Add water to entire mixture.
Cover casserole dish and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to a boil the sugar, milk and coconut.
Punch holes in hot cake with handle of wooden spoon or fork.
Pour hot mixture over hot cake.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: baked clams with walnuts
directions: Chop and mash together the shallots, walnut halves, parsley and vermouth.
Knead in butter, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Spoon topping on each clam.
Cover with freshly grated Parmesan (best quality).
Make a bed of loosely crumpled aluminum foil on a pan.
Arrange clams on foil and bake, loosely covered with a layer of aluminum foil, in a 450° oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
When just barely done, remove foil and brown close to the broiler.
Serves 4.

title: dip for crackers
directions: Shred dried beef; chop the green onions and add to softened cream cheese. Form into a ball. Cover cheese ball with small pieces of dried beef.

title: cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large loaf pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together. Combine the orange juice, butter and eggs together and mix with dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened. Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Place mixture into greased pan and bake for 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of pan comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: grilled chicken tostadas
directions: Combine tomatoes, beans, jalapeno and cumin in skillet. Add cooked chicken. Heat 5 minutes or until thickened.

title: lemon cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix with Cool Whip. Add lemon rind. Beat well.
Add well beaten egg.
Roll in powdered sugar, about 3/4 teaspoon at a time.
Bake on a well-greased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove onto a rack to cool as they tend to stick.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: snowball dessert
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into bowl (or mold) and freeze. Can be cut while frozen or thaw slightly and serve.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix together and mold.
Good for summer as it stays molded in hot weather.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and water; cook over medium heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook gently until caramel is dark and syrup-like.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat; whisk in flour until smooth.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly.
Pour in milk and heat to boiling.

title: zesty italian bake
directions: Brown the hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix (water may need to be added if mixture is too thick).
Cover and simmer for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix with mixer. Spread in 9 x 9 dish. Cover with finely shredded cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain, rinse and chop sauerkraut. Put in a bowl the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Mix until well blended.
Add the vegetables and refrigerate for 2 days.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch casserole, pour the two cans of pineapple, leaving out about 1/2 the juice.
Sprinkle the flour-sugar mixture all over, then sprinkle the cheese.

title: aunt jo's easy pie (lemon icebox)
directions: Mix and pour into prepared crumb or plain pie crust and top with Cool Whip when served.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add just enough mayonnaise to make it creamy.
Add a little ketchup for color.
Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: scrabble cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, pour pineapple and juice, and then spread the cherry pie filling over the pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over the entire top of the filling.
Slice margarine in small slices over the top of the dry mix.
If desired, add walnuts or pecans on top of the margarine. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: crispy ranch chicken
directions: Place crushed potato chips on a sheet of wax paper. Sprinkle on pepper, if desired.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve water and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze in 2 gallon container.
Before serving, thaw to slush and add 2 (28 ounce) bottles ginger ale.
Makes 60 (6 ounce) glasses or 75 (4 ounce) cups.

title: guacamole
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add all ingredients except onion.
Process 1 minute or until lumpy.
Stir in onions.
Yields 2 cups.

title: onion pie
directions: Crush crackers and mix butter, melted.
Put in pan saving few tablespoons for top.
Saute onions in 1/4 stick oleo and put on top of crackers.
Make white sauce with cheese melted in it.
Pour over onions.
Put reserved crumbs on top and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: candied cucumbers
directions: Soak whole cucumbers in salt water for 14 days.
Remove from salt water; slice and soak overnight in 1/2 box alum water. Remove from alum water.
Rinse and soak in 1 gallon apple cider vinegar for 6 hours.
Remove from vinegar.
Pour vinegar out.
Put pickles and sugar in layers with spice.
Use 10 pounds sugar.
Let stand in stone or glass jar for several days before using. Pickles do not have to be sealed.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Add all juice of pineapple to cake mix and 2 tablespoons of pineapple.
Bake as directed on box.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Use medium skillet.
Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Empty grease and use same pan.
Saute onion and beef until brown. Remove onion and beef with slotted spoon.
Put in 2-quart casserole and stir in salt.
Discard drippings.
Add cooked bacon. Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet add remaining ingredients and heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Pour into casserole and stir well.
Bake uncovered for 60 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut one squash in half. Scoop out seeds and strings.
Place in baking dish, cut side down.
Add a little water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Fill cavity with dabs of butter, brown sugar and pecans. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, layer lettuce and onions.
Spoon 1/2 cup mayonnaise evenly on top.
Layer celery, green pepper and peas. Spread remaining mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese and bacon over top.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Add water chestnuts.
Toss before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, cornstarch and sugar together.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Return to stove.
Bring to boil and continue boiling and stirring until thick; cool.
Add about 3 cups sliced strawberries. Pour into baked and cooled pie crust.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar and oil,
Add soda to milk; salt to flour and mix all to sugar/oil mixture.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs and raisin
bran.
Bake as many muffins as needed.
Batter keeps 6 weeks refrigerated.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 3 pie shells. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix soda in small amount buttermilk.
Mix together bran, flour, sugar and salt; add slightly beaten eggs.
Add oil, rest of buttermilk and soda solution.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand until thickened.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 2 months.
When ready to bake, pour into muffin tins lined with paper.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon (leave whole). Saute onions in drippings. Add rest of ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add clams. Heat thoroughly. Remove bacon and serve.

title: debbie's famous barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and adjust seasoning to taste, especially vinegar.
Use as a basting sauce on all meats.
Warm in microwave or saucepan before using as a table condiment.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Add flavorings; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a skillet over medium-low heat.
Add next 7 ingredients and cook until veggies are tender, stirring frequently (about 10 minutes).

title: chocolate zucchini cake with chocolate chip topping
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and buttermilk; mix well.
Add measured dry ingredients, then grated zucchini.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: miniature mounds balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Roll into balls. Let sit in the refrigerator overnight.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: one cup cookie
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Stir until blended.
Remove from heat and pour over 4 c. rice krispies. Stir until coated and press half in bottom of pan.
Melt 6 oz chocolate chips, 2 Tbsp butter, 1 Tbsp water, 1 c. powdered sugar, in top of double boiler.
Stir until chips are well blended.
Pour this over the chilled cereal mixture.
Spread rest of cereal over the top.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef on medium-high.
Drain extra grease off of ground beef.
Melt Velveeta cheese into ground beef.
Add margarine to make mixture loose.
If you desire dip to be thinner, add a few drops of milk slowly!

title: raisin exquisite pie
directions: Cover raisins with hot water; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine raisins with remaining ingredients, mixing well.

title: my grandmother's slaw(no fat - low calorie)
directions: Stir vinegar and sugar into finely grated (or chopped) cabbage.
Then use your hands to squeeze the mixture over and over for about 2 minutes.
The bruising of the cabbage allows it to absorb the vinegar mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bounty rice
directions: Saute beef, onions and green peppers.
Stir in tomatoes, seasonings, rice and cabbage.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together; add the eggs and beat well.
Sift the dry ingredients together and mix into the creamed mixture.
Mix all together very well.
Add the fruit and nuts and blend all together.
Put bar mixture into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cooled, cut into bars.

title: ray's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts or whole chicken, celery and onion in pressure cooker or broil.
Cook thin noodles per package instructions.
Saute butter, onion, celery, bell pepper, poultry seasoning and garlic powder or granules.
Mix all ingredients together in baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with chicken.
Cover with soups, mayonnaise and onion salt.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: egg-strata
directions: Butter bread on both sides. Alternate layers of bread, sausage and cheese. Two layers are usually enough to fill a 13 x 10 x 2 baking dish.
End with cheese on top. Mix eggs, milk and seasoning; pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Cook in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: linda's walnuts
directions: Boil 6 cups water in large pan.
Add walnuts; bring to boil. Boil 1 minute.
Drain and rinse.
Drain well.
Toss with sugar until well coated.
Fry in hot oil.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and milk; when boiling, add marshmallows.
When melted, add coconut and spread over warm cake. Place in fridge to cool.

title: chocolate berry pie
directions: Spread softened ice cream into bottom of crust.
Freeze until firm.
Spread fudge sauce evenly over ice cream.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand approximately 30 minutes before serving.
Garnish with strawberries and drizzle with fudge sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: south dakota baked dinner
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add the chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add the carrots and tomatoes.
Mix and add the potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are soft.

title: three-step cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions, using a 9 x 13 inch baking pan. While hot, poke entire top with fork and spread Eagle Brand milk over top. Cool completely. Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and eggs.
Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce plus 2 1/2 cups water.
Put 1/2 sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Top with about half of noodles, overlapping slightly.
Spread half of cottage cheese mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with about a third of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers as follows:
1 1/2 cups sauce, remaining noodles, remaining cottage cheese, another third of Mozzarella, remaining sauce and remaining cheese.
Seal tightly with foil and place on cookie sheet (makes a large batch and tends to run over).
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Pour peaches in dish. Mix flour and milk together.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour over peaches and stir. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Batter can be used with apples, pears and berries.

title: onion-roasted potatoes(1993 taster's luncheon)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan.
Discard bag.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Garnish, if desired, with chopped fresh parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blondies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook until peanuts are done, then add soda.
Stir and pour on greased pans.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and soup into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Heat in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle casserole with the can of French onions.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg whites with salt; add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add milk. Fold yolks in white mixture.
Dip 8 slices of bread in mixture and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and bake 5 minutes more.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine Wesson oil and onions together and simmer until soft; add balance of recipe and bring to a boil.

title: citrus frost
directions: In blender, combine orange sherbet, tangerine juice concentrate, ice cubes and 1 cup cold water.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Pour into 6 tall glasses.
Pour carbonated beverage down sides of glasses.
Stir gently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place partially thawed potatoes in a greased casserole dish. Mix next 7 ingredients and pour on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle corn flakes and remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix altogether and fry.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix; pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: frosted pineapple cookies
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Set pineapple aside; set juice aside for frosting.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and buttermilk together.
Stir in dry ingredients just to incorporate (do not overmix, should not be smooth).
Stir in melted butter; cook on 400° grill.
May be used for waffles also.

title: mustard base barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 25 minutes and stir.
Store in airtight container.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes until done.
Beat with margarine, softened cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until melted (15 to 20 minutes).

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion, garlic and beef until brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, salt, basil, sugar, pepper and bay leaf and simmer uncovered about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Spread 1/2 cup meat sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, starting with noodles. Make 3 layers, each of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Blend apricots, coconut (1 cup) and pecans together in a large bowl.
Stir in condensed milk.
Shape into small balls and roll in remaining coconut.
Let stand in air until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Mix in other ingredients in the order listed.
Stir.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside. Combine black beans, tomatoes and avocado. Stir dressing with bean mixture and serve. Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Cut beef in very small pieces.
Add diced onion to beef and fry until onion is cooked.
Add soup and 1/2 can of water to meat and onions.
Add cream and heat.
Add flour to water to make paste.
Add flour paste to meat and stir until thickened.
Serve hot over rice or noodles.

title: pasta with fresh asparagus
directions: Boil a pot of water for pasta and begin cooking.
Spinach and egg fettuccine is especially good with this dish.
Clean asparagus and slice across stalks in 1/2-inch pieces.
In wok (or large frypan), heat oil and garlic; then add cut-up asparagus.
Stir-fry about 3 minutes.

title: apple cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Put apples in bowl.
Add sugar and mix.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add egg and oil.
Sift and measure flour.
Mix all ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Put Crisco, milk, sugar and salt on stove.
Get lukewarm.
Add flour.
Mix and knead.
Let set 15 minutes.
Knead and roll.
Let stand 15 minutes, then bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: banana shake(low carb)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender until creamy. Makes 1 serving.

title: coated peanuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add brown sugar. Beat until stiff. Cover all pecan halves. Drop by halves on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for about 25 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: easy coconut icing
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Melt fat in a shallow roasting pan in the oven.
Meanwhile, wash the chicken and dry with paper towels.
Place the flour and seasonings in a plastic bag.
Drop in 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time,
hold the bag closed and shake, coating the pieces.
Place the floured chicken in the baking pan in a single layer, skin side down.
Bake for 30 minutes,
turn the chicken skin side up and continue to bake for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: grandma eichler's no bake cookies(no bakes)
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, then boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: taco stack
directions: Let cream cheese soften, mix taco seasoning mix and cream cheese.
Spread onto a medium-size platter.
Top cream cheese mixture with taco sauce, followed by lettuce, tomato and shredded cheese.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: sweet pickle chips
directions: Drain and rinse pickles. Slice pickles 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Stir into sugar mixture. (Do not use metal container or spoon.) Let stand 24 hours at room temperature; stir occasionally. Put into jars and pour juice evenly into each jar. Store in refrigerator one to two weeks.

title: luscious layer bars
directions: Blend cake mix, oleo, sour cream and eggs.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased and floured large jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch). Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine coconut and milk; gently spread over base.
Return to oven.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool slightly and frost.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well.
Heat butter in skillet. Beat eggs and pour buttermilk into beaten eggs.
Mix good with sugar.
Add milk; mix together well with the blueberries.

title: vanilla wafer crumb cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar gradually.
(The long beating makes the cake.)
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and the sweet milk.
Fold in the crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Put in a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon herb chicken breasts(great on the grill)
directions: Wash chicken breasts, pat dry, sprinkle generously with garlic powder and oregano.
In large bowl, preferably with airtight lid, squeeze juice of lemon and stir in 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Add chicken, place lid on bowl and shake.
If possible let chicken marinate awhile.
Cook on the grill until done or cook at 350° in oven (or toaster oven).
Good served as an entree or as a sandwich.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder; mix well and fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: simple homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and finish filling 1 gallon freezer with milk until 3/4 full.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook sauce 60 minutes or longer.
Use Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese, about 1/2 pound of each for topping.

title: broiled garlic shrimp
directions: Preheat broiler.
Wash and dry shrimp.
Pour margarine in a shallow baking pan and add lemon juice, onion, garlic and pepper. Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Broil for 5 minutes, turn and broil 5 more minutes.
Serve on platter with strained pan juices. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 5; about 2 1/2 ounces shrimp per serving.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Brown butter in saucepan over medium heat until golden brown, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Cool.
Beat corn syrup, sugar and eggs in bowl.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Stir in pecans and browned butter.

title: banana pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box less milk (instant). Cut bananas in quarters and place on bottom of chocolate crust pie.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours, until pudding hardens and put chocolate Cool Whip on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken with the onion, salt and pepper until chicken is tender. Cool. Take chicken off bones.
Cook the vermicelli spaghetti in the chicken broth until tender. Add the cheese, peas, soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix together and bake until bubbly.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes until soft.
Mix all other ingredients except paprika.
Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scrape most of the potato
from the skins and add to the mixture. Beat.
Spoon the mixture into the shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Freeze.
This may be stored for days, well covered.

title: chocolate chip butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Combine flour and soda in a warm bowl.
Mix well with a wire whisk; set aside.

In large bowl use an electric mixer to blend the sugar and butter. Add egg and vanilla; beat at medium speed until light and smooth. Scrape down the sides of the bowl, then add the flour mixture, pecans and chocolate chips.
Blend at low speed until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Transfer batter into prepared pan and level top with a rubber spatula.
Bake in center of oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean, but center is still soft.
Cool on rack to room temperature.
Cut with sharp knife into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Makes about 16 bars.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and margarine with 1 1/4 cups of boiling water and let stand 20 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix the other ingredients, then mix with the oatmeal, margarine and water mixture.
Mix well and pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in crushed bananas and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: syrup for sweet dills
directions: Heat and pour hot over 2 quarts dills, sliced.
Put in refrigerator.
Syrup can be reused once.
A good way to use old dills.

title: heavenly easter delight
directions: Mix together and serve frozen.

title: two fruit smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Add enough ice cubes to bring to 4-cup level.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Each serving contains 100 calories/cup.
Nutritious during pregnancy (consult your physician).

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, the broccoli, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Combine berries, lemon juice, rind and water.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to blueberries.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Cook very slowly 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour into cold baked pie shell.
Whip cream cheese and cream until fluffy. Use to garnish pie.

title: shrimp, peas and rice
directions: Add rice and black-eyed peas.
Combine with shrimp mixture. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with green onions.

title: oatmeal harvest cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs, oatmeal mixture, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Drain squash and put in cold water immediately.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Put in crust and dot with butter; add top crust and bake in 400° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: In a quart saucepan, heat 3/4 cup of the milk and butter to scalding.
In a large bowl, pour hot milk mix over stuffing.
Toss to mix well.
Put half of this mixture into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: baked haddock fillets
directions: Spray shallow pan with nonstick coating.
Place fillets in a pan.
Combine ingredients and spoon over fillets.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serves 4.

title: shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Add beaten egg and milk and mix well.
Put in muffin tins and bake at 400° until browned.
Makes 12 and that depends on the size of the muffin tin. Good with any fresh fruit, especially strawberries.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugars and pudding mix; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamy mixture.
Stir in oats.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Combine flour packet from cake mix and cocoa; stir well with wire
whisk.
Prepare
cake
according to package directions. Fold
chocolate flavoring into batter.
Bake according to
package directions.
Sprinkle
cooled
cake with powdered sugar.
Garnish with
strawberries,
if
desired.	Yield:	16 servings (107 calories and 2% fat per serving).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients. Blend into creamed mixture. Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with fork tines. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: violet's salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place breast halves between Saran Wrap. Beat until thin (about 1/4 inch). Sprinkle each breast with condiments.
Place one of the butter sticks in each roll-up. Dust with flour. Dip in beaten egg. Roll in breadcrumbs. Place in Pyrex dish. Pour in wine. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover to brown.

title: peach crisp
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat into a greased 9 inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain the peaches and reserve juice in a medium saucepan.
Add the sugar and cornstarch; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat;
stir in peaches.
Pour into crust.
For topping, combine oats, brown sugar and flour.
Cut in the butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Place potatoes and water in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 10 to 14 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Drain.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream, green pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cook on half power for 7 to 10 minutes, or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix for two 8-inch or 9-inch layers. Allow cakes to cool.
Whip one container of cream, 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon of extract.
Use a serrated knife to cut each cake into two layers.
Line a 2 1/2-quart bowl with plastic wrap. Place one layer in bowl and spread 3 tablespoons of jam over layer and then 1/3 of whipped cream over jam.
Repeat until all layers are used.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap while pressing down layers. Chill in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Whip second container of cream with remaining sugar and extract and a few drops of food coloring.
Invert cake onto plate and cover with whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and brown sugar; mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Slowly add flour, salt and baking soda.
Add chips, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake about 8 minutes.
May be baked as pan cookie.

title: banana shake
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend on high until well blended.
Yields four (1-cup) servings.
Great quickie for teens to make.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Add sour cream.
Combine flour, salt and soda and add mixture to creamed mixture.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt the oleo. Add the milk, egg and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add the coconut, graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Spread over the crackers and cover with whole graham crackers.
Frost with fudge frosting. Let set overnight and cut into bars.

title: hot roll mix
directions: Mix together as for pie crust.

title: quick chicken parmesan
directions: Whatever number of chicken patties needed, cook in microwave according to directions on package.
Place chicken in casserole dish and spoon spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Then add lots of Parmesan cheese and cooked spaghetti.
Top with more sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: three layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown the ground beef, drain and set aside.
Drain the liquid from the corn and set aside.
Cover the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish with a layer of sliced potatoes. Put a layer of the cooked ground beef over the potatoes.
Put a layer of corn over the ground beef.
Continue layering the potatoes, ground beef and corn until all used.
In a bowl, mix the soup and pour over the top of the other ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours, or until potatoes are done.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Serve over ice.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in bottom.
Arrange pineapple halves on top of sugar.
Drain cherries and slice in half.
Put cherry slices on top of each pineapple slice.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over fruit fruit and spread evenly.
Bake for 45 to 48 minutes.
Loosen cake from pan and turn onto platter.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Prepare beef dinner as package directs.
Meanwhile, in large frypan, brown meat in hot oil.
Add onion slices; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms, green pepper, celery, bean sprouts, spinach and soy sauce.
Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add cooked rice.
Mix and serve.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour. Add eggs, vanilla, milk and butter.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: stuffed shells with cheese
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions.
Drain portion of water, allowing shells to remain in warm water.
Mix cheeses, eggs, parsley and salt.
Remove one shell at a time from warm water.
Stuff each shell with mixture, using a tablespoon.
Pour 1/2 jar sauce into shallow casserole.
Arrange stuffed shells in casserole.
Add remaining sauce to top.
Cover; bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until warm through.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in order given.	Top with cheese and potato chips and bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil and debone chicken and cut into pieces.
Crush enough crackers to fill bottom of Pyrex dish.
Layer crackers, chicken and sliced water chestnuts and cover with remaining ingredients that you have mixed together to create a sauce. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked small wild game in sour cream
directions: Soak the meat overnight in salted water.
Dry and roll in flour.
Saute in margarine until browned.
Remove the meat and spread with mustard on all sides.
Saute onion, carrots and mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper to taste; add the garlic powder and then stir in the sour cream over low heat.
Pour the resulting sauce over the meat and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until the meat is tender.

title: fruit delight
directions: Prepare angel cake as directed.
Cool and slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Put layer in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Use about 3 cups of fruit.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well blended.
Beat in chocolate. Add 1 egg; beat on high 5 minutes.
Add second egg; beat on high at least 5 minutes or until all sugar is melted.
Pour in pie shell and chill.
Cool Whip (optional).

title: no fail, no fuss basic gravy
directions: One tablespoon cornstarch equals 2 tablespoons flour.

title: cheezy fries
directions: Cook fries according to package.
Place fries in a big bowl. Sprinkle shredded cheese all over bowl of fries.
Sprinkle bacon bits over top.
Place in the oven until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put the butter and water in a saucepan over heat.
When water boils, add flour all at once.
Stir until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add one unbeaten egg at a time and beat hard.
Continue until eggs are all added.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let sausage mixture cool a little.
Add eggs, beaten well with cheese.
Stir to mix.
Grease cookie sheet and spread dough with hands (to cover pan).
Fill with mixture.
Fold up.
Put seam on bottom.
Let rise and bake.

title: florida-style flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients in a ceramic or glass dish.
Marinate for at least 6 hours (for best flavor) turning steak now and then. Cook on grill until done (about 7 minutes per side).
Allow to stand a few minutes before slicing.
Slice very thin diagonally.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: I Layer:
Break angel food cake in small pieces.

title: mama's pecan pie cake bars
directions: Mix margarine, cake mix and 1 egg together.
Reserve 2/3 cup of this mixture for topping and pat remainder in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix brown sugar, Karo syrup and eggs, vanilla, reserved 2/3 cup of cake mixture and chopped nuts. Pour over partially baked cake.
Return to oven at 375°.
Bake until cake tests done.
Cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: coconut cream cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg; beat with electric or wire beater, until well blended.
Add sour cream, soda and salt.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat well.
Add the coconut, then remaining flour.
Drop with teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pour hot vinegar solution over okra, etc. in the jar.
Seal; do not crowd okra in the jar.
It takes at least three weeks to pickle and get crisp.

title: cottage cheese muffins
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients into bowl and mix in oats and cornflakes.
Beat egg yolk; add fat, cheese and milk.
Pour liquid mixture into a "well" in the dry ingredients and beat.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Bake in muffin tins in a slow oven at 300°, about 1 hour.

title: mother's cookies
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Turn out on floured cloth or board and roll thin; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in moderately hot oven until brown.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Pour into aluminum pan.
Chop onions and peppers (green and red) and place in pan.
Add salt to taste.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine.
Add 2 teaspoons of bacon bits.
Cover with foil and place on hot grill.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Place 6 slices bread on bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Cover with 1 cup Cheddar cheese, broccoli, ham and remaining bread slices, cut in half diagonally.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Blend in milk and mustard; pour over bread.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add sugar and flour; mix well.
Beat eggs.
Add to sugar mixture; mix until smooth.
Add vanilla and milk.
Cook on medium flame, stirring constantly until quite thick.
Remove from burner. Layer the following in a large bowl: one layer of wafers, one layer of sliced bananas and one layer of pudding mixture.
Repeat until all pudding is used.
Top with layer of vanilla wafers. Scrumptious!

title: crockpot chicken breast
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, wine and mushrooms.
Place chicken breast in crockpot.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cut onion into 1/4 inch slices and break apart into rings.
Spread over chicken.
Pour soup mixture over all and spread evenly. Sprinkle some more paprika over top.
Cook on low setting 6-8 hours.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 4-6 servings.

title: italian marble cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Prepare marble cake mix as directed and pour into pan.
In a mixing bowl, mix Ricotta, sugar, 4 eggs and vanilla.
Layer over marble cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Allow cake to cool. Serve.

title: potato pie with brandy hard sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, beat at high speed the egg whites into soft peak.
With mixer at low speed, beat egg yolks, potatoes, milk, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, cloves and salt until well blended.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour mixture in crust and bake until set.

title: sylvia's stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half (1/2); scoop out seed with spoon. In greased pan, bake face down at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cook bacon; remove and crumble.
Retain grease.
In retained grease, saute onions, bell peppers, hot peppers and tomatoes until tender. Add milk, cheese, butter, sugar and crumbled bacon.
Take squash and scoop out the squash; save shell.
Mix squash with ingredients.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix preserves, soup and dressing.
Pour over chicken. Marinate for several hours or overnight.
Put chicken in casserole.
Cover with marinade.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° until done.
Uncover and brown.

title: italio spaghetti
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions; drain grease off.
Return to skillet. Reduce temperature.
Add thyme, oregano, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Mix in browned beef.
Pour tomato juice over mixture.
Add broken spaghetti.
Press spaghetti into mixture until it is covered with juice.
Cover skillet and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: sesame twist quick bread(three star)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form dough into smooth ball and knead 30 seconds of floured board.
Roll into rope 2 inches thick and cut into 16 pieces.
Roll each piece 8 inches long, lapping ends.
Fold in half, twist once and pinch ends together. Place on buttered baking sheet; brush with slightly beaten whole egg.
Sprinkle with lots of sesame seed.
Bake in upper third of preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: don's rotisserie chicken
directions: Put green pepper, salt, pepper, margarine and onion inside chicken.
Lay bacon over breast area and tie chicken well.
Put on spit and rub a little margarine over chicken.
Put on rotisserie and cook on medium or low until well done.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pie crust into pie pan as directed on package.
Combine all other ingredients (except vegetables, etc.)
in mixing bowl and mix lightly.
Add vegetables, bacon, meats, etc., if desired.
Pour into crust.
Mixture will look lumpy due to Cheddar cheese.
Put in oven and bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Quiche should have a slight brown coating when cooked completely.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Saute in oil the onions, garlic and pepper.
Flour the eggplant and brown on all sides in the oil.
Add the vegetables. Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes until just barely tender.
Add grated cheese.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: a b c sweet treats
directions: You will need waxed paper.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Place chops in a roasting pan; mix other ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and place by heaping spoonfuls into greased skillet.
Flatten into patties.
Makes 8 patties.

title: koinonia granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt in a large roasting pan the oil, margarine, molasses, vanilla, brown sugar, honey and salt.
When mixed, let cool slightly and add the oats, sesame seed, chopped nuts, garage nuts, wheat germ, coconut and sunflower seeds.
Stir thoroughly. Bake in shallow pans for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir every 5 to 7 minutes.
After granola has cooled, add the raisins.
Very good as a snack.

title: waist watchin' popcorn snack
directions: In a large bowl, combine hot popped corn, nuts, pretzels and bran squares.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine with mustard. Pour over popcorn mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Sprinkle herb and spice mix over coated corn and toss again. Spread coated corn on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes. Serve immediately or store in airtight container.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain all canned ingredients.
Put in bowl.
Add bell pepper, onion, and Italian dressing.
Cover and let sit overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: cool cucumber rice salad
directions: Combine rice, cucumber, green pepper and radishes.
Blend remaining ingredients (dressing, mustard and pepper).
Toss dressing mixture lightly with rice mixture and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine margarine and sugars.
Add eggs; mix well. Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal, pecans and coconut.
Chill dough.
Make into rolls, 1 1/2 inches.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze rolls.
Slice thin and bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Leave plenty of space between cookies on cookie sheet; they spread a lot.

title: betty's banana nut cake
directions: Cream
together eggs, margarine and sugar.
Add bananas. Into another
bowl,
sift
together
flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture,
a
little
at
a time, to sugar-butter mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into a well greased
and floured angel cake pan and bake for 1 hour at 300°. Can be frozen.

title: rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in fat.
Mix with warm water.
Let rise 1 hour or until it doubles its size.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons flour and knock down.
Put in refrigerator with cover and use as needed.

title: velvet angel pie
directions: Melt chocolate with the coffee in saucepan over low heat until blended; cool.
Stir in vanilla, then fold into whipped cream. Fill meringue shell.
Refrigerate overnight or approximately 12 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped cream, shaved chocolate and pecan halves.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all
ingredients; place in iron skillet and bake in oven at 400° until done.

title: sun-dried tomato dip
directions: Combine tomatoes, water, garlic and herbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass or ceramic dish and cover tightly with microwave plastic wrap.
Cook at 100% in a high-wattage microwave oven for 8 minutes. Prick plastic to release steam.
Remove from oven and uncover; stir well.
Re-cover and cook for 8 minutes longer.
Prick plastic to release steam.
Remove from oven and uncover; stir well and allow to stand, stirring occasionally, until cool and most of liquid is absorbed.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart dish; pour both oils over tomato mixture.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap; cook for 5 minutes more. Prick plastic; remove from oven and uncover.
Stir and leave until cool.
Transfer to food processor and puree until smooth, scraping down sides of bowl.
Serve at room temperature with thinly sliced Italian bread, crackers or cut up vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator (tightly covered) for up to one month.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Measure flour, salt, baking powder and soda into a sifter. Cream the butter or margarine with sugar until well blended in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour mixture, adding alternately with sour cream and blend well to make a thick batter.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 4 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Spread into 2-inch rounds.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar, if desired.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for about 12 minutes or until light golden around edges.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely on wire racks.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with meringue; brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: This makes a thin batter.
Bake at 400° or 450° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate gem pie
directions: For crust, combine flour, pecans and brown sugar.
In a heavy saucepan, melt shortening and 1 square of chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir into flour mixture until combined.
Mix vanilla and water and sprinkle over mixture while tossing.
Form into a ball.
Roll out to make a 12-inch circle between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Remove waxed paper.
Place crust into a 9-inch pie plate; flute edge.
Prick well.
Bake until surface appears dry. Cool.

title: coconut custard
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Bake in oblong Pyrex dish lightly sprayed with Pam.
Cook in preheated oven at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: microwave parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic.
Cover loosely with Saran Wrap and cook on Full power for 5 minutes in microwave.
Add green pepper, salt and pepper and toss.
Add cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook for 6 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: You will need 1 large bowl.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Cream
butter
and
cream cheese, slowly add flour, then add vanilla.
Good
for any type pie, may also be used for tart shells.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook the
bottom
crust.
Cook butter, water, sugar and cornstarch until it
boils.
Pour
1/2 over bottom crust; pour fresh berries on next, leveling down; next add pie filling and then
top
crust.
Pour
the rest of syrup on top and brown in oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time and continue mixing. Add pumpkin and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Add water and mix by hand well until smooth. Pour into greased loaf pans and bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Watch at the end of baking and cover top with foil if getting too brown.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: "no peek" casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek until it is done.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: mexican cheese soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil potatoes and garlic in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Turn heat to simmer; add butter, milk, tomatoes, chilies, Tabasco and green onions.
Do not allow milk to boil.
When warm, drop in cheese.
As cheese just starts to melt, the soup is ready to serve.
Feeds one Mexican Army.

title: diet butternut squash
directions: Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Mix together, shape into log.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers and vegetables.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Drain and chop tomatoes. Save liquid.
Melt cheese with 2 Tbsp. tomato liquid in microwave or on stove top.
Add 1/3 cup liquid to cheese. Mix everything together in large bowl. Serve cold or at room temperature.
Stir when ready to serve.
Makes a lot.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and Jell-O for 1 minute.
Cool.
Have baked pie shell.
Place strawberries in shell.
Pour the mixture over the strawberries.
Refrigerate to set.
Before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix and bake in unbaked pie shell until firm.

title: lumpiaphillipines
directions: Brown the beef and drain. Mix together all remaining ingredients except lumpia wrappers. Cook for 20-30 minutes, drain away excess liquid. Sit for 10 minutes before wrapping. Put some of the mixture onto a wrapper, fold over each side, then roll up. Making a little package. Fry in the oil until golden brown.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Blanch all ingredients until al dente.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat together or mix in blender; refrigerate.

title: cinnamon munch
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon, set aside.
Melt butter over low heat in skillet.
Add Chex and stir to coat.
Heat for 5 minutes more, sprinkle with half of sugar/cinnamon mixture and stir to coat cereal pieces.
Add remaining sugar/cinnamon and stir. Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: chicken and vegetable salad(servings:  6)
directions: Cook chicken breast.
Add Japanese cucumbers and bean sprouts. Mix these ingredients.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken in food processor.
If you are going to use your chicken salad for sandwiches, chop medium fine.
To serve on lettuce, chop and leave it in medium-small chunks.
Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine cake mix, nuts and melted butter. Crumble mixture over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: southern cannon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Roll into walnut-size balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper. Serve hot!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and place in prepared 9 x 3 cake pan. Top with 1 cup crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: sharon's gourmet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes (cook whole in skin).
Cool thoroughly.
Shred potatoes coarsely.
Combine mild and sharp cheeses, 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup sweet milk; cook over low heat until cheeses melt.
Add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Put shredded potatoes in 9 x 13-inch glass pan, pour mixture over potatoes and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: khyar bil-laban (lebanese)(cucumber-yogurt salad)
directions: Mash garlic with salt and fresh mint in bowl.
Add yogurt, blending well.
Peel and cut cucumbers in half lengthwise, then slice in thin half rounds.
Add cucumbers to yogurt mixture.
Fold together gently.
This is especially refreshing in summer.
Serves 4.
Garnish with fresh mint.

title: honey mustard baked beans
directions: In small saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add beans and simmer for 2 minutes. Serves 2 to 4.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir sliced zucchini and chopped onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine eggs and cheese; stir into zucchini mixture.

title: blueberry cream cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill muffin tin with cupcake liners. In processor, whip cream cheese, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and butter and blend.
Combine next 5 ingredients and beat into cream cheese mixture until well blended.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into muffin tins.
Fill 3/4 full.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: dressing
directions: Combine cornbread and biscuits in large baking dish and pour 4 cups chicken broth over cornbread and biscuits. Let soak. Chop onions and celery. Cook onion and celery in margarine over low heat until tender. Mix together remaining ingredients. Add celery, onion, eggs, salt, pepper, sage and broth to first mix. Stir as little as possible. (Overstirring will cause dressing to be soggy.) Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, add other ingredients and cook over hot water until the mixture is of a jelly-like consistency.
Pour into pastry shell; cover with meringue and bake in a slow oven about 15 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Push down firmly.
Melt marshmallows in milk in double boiler. Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on crumb mixture.
Spread pie mix.
Chill 4 or more hours.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut the cabbage very fine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Stir well and let stand for 5 minutes. Drop lard onto a hot iron kettle; then the cabbage, stirring briskly until cabbage is quite tender.
Add cream and remove kettle from the fire.
Then stir in cider vinegar.

title: chicken and broccoli with mushroom sauce
directions: Mix margarine and flour together in saucepan.
Cook briefly over medium heat.
Blend in chicken broth, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Stir in mushrooms and their liquid. Season to taste.
Place broccoli pieces in a shallow baking pan. Cover with sliced chicken and pour mushroom sauce over all.
Top with parsley and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 15 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: facelift casserole(breakfast casserole)
directions: Brown and drain sausage and set aside.
Beat eggs and milk, salt and mustard.
Gently stir in bread, cheese and sausage.
Put in 8 x 12-inch buttered pan and refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan tart
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat first 2 ingredients until fluffy. Stir in combined flour and 3/4 cup oats.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch tart pan or pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Beat eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar, 1/4 cup margarine and bourbon until blended.
Stir in 1 cup pecans and remaining 2/3 cup oats.
Pour into crust.
Decorate top with pecan halves.
Bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate covered grapes
directions: Wash grapes and drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Do this several hours before ready to dip.
If one drop of water gets into melted mixture, it will cause the chocolate to harden up and become unusable.
Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper; set aside.
In a small saucepan combine chocolate pieces and shortening.
Heat and stir over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Holding grape bunch by stem, dip grapes partially into melted chocolate.
If necessary spoon over grapes to coat.
Let excess drip off; place on prepared cookie sheet.
Chill until chocolate is firm, about 30 minutes or up to 6 hours.
Makes 1 bunch (about twenty, 3-5 grape servings).

title: grandmother's old-time egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° until golden brown.
Dust top of custard with cinnamon.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the top of the peaches (do not stir; this is the crust!), covering well.
You may not need the entire box.
Sprinkle the cinnamon sugar over the top and then follow with the melted butter.
Cook at 325° for about 45 minutes or until the top browns.

title: mother's swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all well.
Brown slightly in fat.
Add 1/2 cup or more water.
Cover tightly and simmer about 1 hour, until tender.
Or, bake in oven for 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 15 meatballs.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in hot oil.
Remove chops.
Add celery and onion and cook lightly, about 3 minutes.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients; add chops.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: short ribs of beef
directions: Saute onion in butter and add the mushroom soup, mushrooms and 1 can of water.
Add chicken or turkey, salt, pepper and curry powder.
Mix well and heat.
Serve this on Minute rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: ham-aghetti casserole
directions: Place 1-inch pieces of bacon into a 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes. Remove half the fat.
Add ham, tomatoes, spaghetti, onions, green pepper, salt and pepper. Stir well.
Cover.
Microwave on High 18 to 20 minutes until spaghetti is tender, stirring after 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, uncovered, until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Form in a meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Pour favorite tomato sauce or gravy over and serve.
Enjoy.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: italian sausage
directions: Cut sausage into pieces.
Slice onion and pepper.
Fry in covered pan until browned.
Place noodles in 6 quarts boiling water.
Return to second boil, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Add sausage mixture and spaghetti sauce and pour over drained noodles.
Makes approximately 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: baked meat balls
directions: Combine beef with onion, green pepper, egg, seasonings and rice cereal. Form into 10 balls. Roll balls in flour and brown in hot shortening.
Place balls in a large casserole and pour tomato soup which has been diluted with 1 can of hot water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Break eggs lightly, then add condensed milk to the yolk and beat again.
Add lime juice and beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue and bake in a slow oven until meringue is brown.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar; boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk, stirring until milk comes to a boil.
Cool.
Add sugar, beating after each addition, until spreadable.

title: pineapple nut squares
directions: Melt butter and cream with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Drain pineapple well.
Add butter, sugar and eggs, mixing alternately with flour mixture.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Blend ingredients. Roll into balls and mash with fork. Chill for 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. (These freeze well.)

title: icebox cake no. 1
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Drop one egg yolk at a time in the sugar and butter.
Beat whites and add to the above.

title: come for coffee cake(quick and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place brown sugar in a pot on the stove top at medium heat.
Add eggs and stir.
Sugar should start to dissolve.
Stir in the flour, one cup at a time.
Add vanilla to taste and stir.
Add pecans and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased with oleo.
Bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer one-third of graham crackers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Combine pudding mix and 3 cups of milk in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer until blended, about 2 minutes. Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon half of mixture on graham crackers.
Repeat layers, ending with graham crackers.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, margarine or butter and sugar. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: homemade pancake syrup
directions: Mix brown sugar, water, butter and salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in maple flavoring.
Serve warm.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add buttermilk.
Turn onto floured surface and knead very briefly.
Pinch off and roll biscuits.
Place in greased pie plate with sides touching.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Do not overbake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop lean beef and green onion tops.
Mix all ingredients. Shape into ball.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: mushroom potatoes
directions: Peel,
slice
and cook potatoes.
Arrange in glass pan; add salt.
Cook soup, milk, margarine and cheese until cheese melts. Pour
over
potatoes.
Sprinkle
with
cracker crumbs. Bake until mixture bubbles.

title: rice side dish
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: tina's tasty tater salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, adding potatoes last. Chill and serve.
Recipe can be halved.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add sugar to cream cheese.
Mix well after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in greased 8-inch pan. Chill several hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: 1, 2, 3 cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Can be mixed in same pan as baked in.) Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1 (9 x 13-inch) or 2 (8-inch round) pans.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple juice and all in small pan.
Heat until Jell-O is dissolved.
Do not boil.
Let cool until slightly thick.
Add buttermilk and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.
(You may use diet Jell-O if you so desire.)

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar and melted butter.
Press into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower into bite size pieces in large bowl.
Add black olives and diced onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Stir well.
Cover bowl and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs; pat in pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and butter; beat 15 minutes and pour on crust.
Slice bananas on this and pour pineapple on top.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar and vinegar; bring to boil.
Add this mixture to beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat good; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: turkey drumsticks
directions: Put all the soups in a big bowl.
For each can of soup, add 1/2 can of water.
Mix well and pour over the drumsticks.
Bake for about 2 hours in a covered pan at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spinach dip casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook spinach until just done. Drain well.
Mix spinach with cream cheese, butter and salt.
Put in casserole dish and cover with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spring egg rolls pancakes
directions: Mix flour, salt, eggs and water until smooth.
Lightly oil 6-inch skillet and heat.
Pour as little of the batter as necessary to cover the bottom into the skillet.
Bake over very low heat until set, then turn over for a few seconds.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup mushroom soup with remaining ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Blend remaining soup, 1/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons drippings.
Heat and stir often.
Serve with loaf.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt the two Hershey bars in a double boiler.
Fold in Cool Whip and put in the baked crust overnight with a few almonds on top, if desired.
Put in the freezer.

title: sour cream and squash casserole
directions: Cook together squash, carrot and onion, then drain.
Place squash mixture and alternate with mixture of cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Bake at 200° for 30 minutes.
During last few minutes, place grated cheese on top.
Secret is slowing cooking.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: The rest is the same as for jam.

title: macaroni vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni and vegetables according to directions.
Cool. Mix in small bowl the Ranch dressing, mustard, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Mix radishes and onions with macaroni and vegetables. Cover with dressing and mix well.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Cover; let marinate in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: two-corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Saute pepper and onion in butter until soft. Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake until set.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well. Shape into 1-inch meat balls. Brown for 15 to 20 minutes in hot oven (450°). Combine sauce and juice of pineapple in skillet. Heat and add meatballs. Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes. Add pineapple chunks and olives. Simmer at least 15 minutes. The longer they simmer, the better they become. Cook about 2 hours with pineapple. Add olives the last 45 minutes. Yield: about 6 dozen meatballs. Crock-pot is the best to cook them in.

title: mayor sal mancini's summer rice salad
directions: Cook rice and drain well.
Follow directions on the Good Seasons packets.
Combine all ingredients while rice is warm. Chill. Serves 10.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour and white and brown sugar to eggs, beating until well blended.
Add melted butter, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Fills one pie shell.

title: butter dumplings
directions: Mix together egg, butter, salt, spices, parsley and chives; then stir in flour. Let batter stand at room temperature for about an hour. Bring broth, soup or salted water to gentle boil, then using a teaspoon drop batter into liquid. When dumplings rise to surface they are cooked. Makes approximately 20.

title: almond curried fruit
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a
x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle the fruit with almonds.
Combine butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Top
fruit
with brown sugar mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: last-minute rolls
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before dinner:
Into scalded milk in large bowl, stir sugar, salt, and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm.
In small bowl, sprinkle or crumble yeast into warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir into lukewarm milk mixture.
Add flour; stir until well blended, about 1 minute.
Cover with towel and let rise until doubled.
Stir batter well, then beat vigorously about 1/2 minute.
Fill greased muffin pan cups or pinch off and put in pan. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: nutty delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread almonds in a single layer in baking pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly toasted. Remove from oven and cool completely, about 30 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°. Generously grease 2 baking pans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in oil.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add broccoli.
Cook until tender in skillet. Place in casserole dish and cover with cream of mushroom soup, undiluted.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted, 10 or 15 minutes.

title: popsicles(kids recipe)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Store in closed containers.

title: bean and rib soup
directions: Sort
and
wash
beans;
place
in
a large Dutch oven. (Cast-iron, if
you
have one.) Fill with water 2 inches above beans and
bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cover and let soak 1 hour; drain and remove.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots
until
tender.
Add onions, green peppers, salt and pepper.
Heat
just
to boiling the remaining ingredients and pour over carrot mixture.
Chill well.

title: guacamole taco dip
directions: Put a layer of bean dip, followed by layer of guacamole, onions, cheese, olives, peppers and tomato.
End with a layer of cheese.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: mexican plate bean dip
directions: Spread bean dip over plate.
Mix taco mix and salad dressing together.
Spread over bean dip.
Put shredded lettuce on top, then put tomatoes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.
Serve the dip with chips.

title: lanita's red rice
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in bacon grease. Stir in cold rice, then tomato sauce and crumbled bacon.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Cut lemon into about 6 slices.
Put lemon, lemon juice, sugar and water into a food processor or blender.
Blend until lemon is in very small pieces.
Strain the mixture into a pitcher and discard the pulp.
Serve well chilled.

title: broccoli-carrot stir-fry
directions: For sauce, in a bowl, stir together orange juice, dry sherry and cornstarch; set aside.

Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat. Add cooking oil (add more cooking oil as necessary during cooking). Stir-fry ginger root in hot oil for 15 seconds. Add carrots and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add broccoli and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until
crisp-tender. Push vegetables from the center of the wok or skillet.
Stir sauce; add to center of wok. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir for 1 minute more. Stir in vegetables and walnuts to coat. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: If using self-rising flour, do not use soda. Mix all ingredients together. Bake 35 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: pumpkin dessert bread
directions: Place dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center, then add all of the other ingredients.
Put into 2 loaf pans, which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine water, spices and sugar in large saucepan; boil, uncovered for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except lemon slices; heat until warm, but do not boil.
Strain.
Serve in mugs with fresh lemon slices.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat broiler; in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish, arrange shrimp on bottom.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour mixture over shrimp and stir.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat until shrimp are golden brown.
Usually 2 to 4 minutes.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and save for other use.
Clean caps and brush outsides with melted butter.
Mix rest of ingredients and mound into caps.
Place onto broiling pan and broil 6 inches from heat, approximately 3 to 5 minutes until bubbling and brown.

title: simmered franks
directions: Heat jelly and mustard over low heat. Cut wieners up. Pour mixture over wieners. Cook in slow cooker 2 or 3 hours.
Serve hot.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in water.
Add egg, salt, sugar and flour. Work until smooth.
Let rise.
Work again.
Let rise and make out into rolls.
Let rise and bake in oven at 350° until light brown or to your desire.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Remove skin and debone salmon.
Blend all the ingredients. Mold or shape as you like.
Roll in parsley and pecans, attractive and delicious on crackers.

title: party dip or breakfast bread treat
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef together.
Add spices.
Add cheese and let melt over medium heat.
Place on loaves and freeze. Use as a party dip.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients real good, then add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: cracker candy
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar and boil for 2-3 min. Line 13x9 in pan with saltine crackers. Pour sugar mixture. Bake for 5 min. at 375°. Let cool a few minutes. Melt almond bark and pour over brickle. Top with chopped pecans. Let cool completely, then break apart.

title: chicken with eggplant in garlic sauce
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry. Transfer chicken to plate.
To same skillet add eggplant, garlic and ginger; stir in beef broth and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and sesame oil.
Add mixture and radishes.
Cook until sauce thickens and comes to a boil.
Add chicken; heat through.
Sprinkle with crushed red pepper.
Makes 6 servings; per serving 425 calories.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in ungreased casserole dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, cinnamon and egg yolk to butter and sugar; mix well.
Put into ungreased 11 x 16-inch pan. Pour unbeaten egg white over top and spread with back of spoon. Pour off excess.
Press nuts over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven.
Cut after 3 to 5 minutes.

title: fried rice (japanese)
directions: Mix eggs, 1 tsp. DASHI sauce, sugar and pepper until well blended.
Heat skillet, add sesame oil, and egg mixture.
Scramble and remove from skillet.
Add vegetable oil to the hot skillet. Stir in green onion, ginger and egg mixture.
Add cooked rice and ham until crisp and hot.
Mix with 2 Tbsp. DASHI sauce and a little pepper to taste.
If you prefer, you can use any kind of meat instead of ham.

title: coriander and mint chutney
directions: Clean and wash coriander, mint, chili, tomato and onion.
Put small amounts of each in blender and blend.
Add yogurt and salt a little at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Store in a container with a tight lid.
Will last approximately 2 to 3 weeks, just stir each time you use it.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar with shortening until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift cake flour before measuring, then sift with baking powder 3 times.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to buttermilk, then add alternately with flour mixture to creamed sugar and shortening.
Mix in finely mashed bananas.
Pour in greased, floured pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream shortening and add salt and vanilla.
Add rest of sugar, then egg yolks.
Beat.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and 1/3 cup milk. Fold in egg whites and blueberries (dusted with flour).
Sprinkle sugar over batter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Put into a large kettle and bring to boil.
Fill jars with okra, as desired.
Hot peppers may be added also as taste desires. Pour boiling liquid over okra.
Fill jars to neck and seal.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes and let stand for a few hours or overnight, still in their jackets.
Peel potatoes and mash them or put through a ricer, then add the eggs and flour.
Roll the mixture into little balls.
Chill in refrigerator for about an hour before cooking.
Cook in lightly salted water that is just under the boiling point.
When dumplings are done, will rise to top.
Serve hot with melted brown butter and crumbs.

title: queen of hearts tarts
directions: Cream together thoroughly the butter and sugar.
Stir in the egg yolk and vanilla.
Sift together the flour and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into 3 dozen small balls and dip each into unbeaten egg white.
Roll in chopped nuts (pecans or peanuts) and place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Do not flatten balls.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
