After baking 10 minutes, remove pan from oven and with a thimble, make a dent into each cookie.
Return pan to oven.
Work as quickly as possible and if the thimble sticks, dip into cold water.
When cookies are done, remove to cooling rack and fill each dent, while warm, with jam or marmalade.
A tart jam is best (plum, apricot or pineapple).

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor or blender; mix until blended.
Taste to determine amount of hot sauce you wish to add.
If it's too thick for dipping, add a little water.
Make ahead so flavors mingle.
Serve with low calorie tortilla chips. Contains 62 calories in 1/4 cup.

title: azar's strawberry pie
directions: Stir and cook water, corn syrup and cornstarch until clear and thick.
Add jello and some red food coloring.
Cool and pour over berries in pie shell.

title: old lady cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and beat thoroughly. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg, allspice, cloves, cinnamon and salt together 3 times.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake in a greased tube pan in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes one (9-inch) cake.

title: cheese straws
directions: Heat
oven
to
Prepare
pie
crust as directed, stirring
in cheese with cold water.
Roll each half into 13 x 10-inch rectangle; place on ungreased baking sheets.

title: the very best spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in a large 8-quart saucepan; pour off fat. Add onion and continue to saut until onion is golden.
Add wine and deglaze pan.
Add tomato using just enough water to rinse out each can.
Add other seasonings and simmer 5 to 6 hours or until sauce is desired thickness.
If it gets too thick, thin with tomato sauce.
Thick sauce is best for pasta and meat dishes. Thinner sauce is better for lasagna or stuffed pastas.
Can even be used as a pizza sauce.
Will freeze well.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: sour cream candy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring slowly until sugar melts.
Then boil without stirring over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
(Do not stir.)
Add vanilla; beat until it starts to lose its gloss, about 8 minutes.
Add cherries and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: dressing for vegetables
directions: Mix well with hand mixer the first 4 ingredients.
Pour over the raw veggies about 2 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done; cool.

title: layered salad(vegetable)
directions: Layer vegetables in order given.
Seal with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Let set overnight.
Toss to serve.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Melt the chocolate in double boiler.
Sift the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Beat the eggs and gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add oil and chocolate; beat until well blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Place apples in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Stir cornstarch and salt into sugar mixture.
Sprinkle over apples.
Stir together flour and nutmeg.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of water over part of mixture. Toss with fork.
Repeat until all moistened.
Form into a ball and roll dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Place pastry atop apples.
Cut vents in pastry and flute edges.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Brush pastry with milk and sprinkle with reserved sugar mixture.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When once selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist upon keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter; even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good.

title: sausage snack wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place sausages on shortest end of each triangle.
Roll up, starting at shortest end and rolling to opposite point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with ketchup and mustard, if desired.
Yields 48 snacks.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries.
In a medium saucepan, add cranberries and 1 cup water.
Cook berries until they pop open.
Take off heat.
Add sugar and jello.
Stir well until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple (juice and all), apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into glass bowl and refrigerate until jelled.
May be topped with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat the margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, stir flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cookies will be slightly moist in centers. Do not overbake.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute hamburger, chopped green pepper and chopped onion together.
Cook until well done.
Add spaghetti and other ingredients.
Put in a casserole and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 370° until well warmed.

title: chocolate chip christmas cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and chips and/or nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12-14 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; cook to form a soft ball.
Add oleo and nuts; continue cooking until it turns brown.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda, stir until it foams.
Pour quickly into a greased pan and break into pieces.

title: butterscotch peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, evaporated milk, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan. Stir over moderate heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add butterscotch chips, peanut butter and vanilla, stirring until smooth. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Chill until fudge is firm. Cut into squares. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: lazy day cabbage rolls
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Serves six.

title: welch cookies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients like pie crust, then add currants, eggs and milk.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cutter or water glass.
Spray with Pam.
Fry on griddle until golden in color. Turn to do other side.
Cool on rack.

title: tuna stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise and remove seeds.
Parboil zucchini in a large pan of salted water until slightly tender.
Test for doneness with skewer.
Combine and mix thoroughly tuna, egg, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper in bowl.
Stuff zucchini with tuna
mixture.
Add tomato sauce and top with bread crumbs.
Place in greased ovenproof dish, or on cookie sheet on top of aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° until heated, about 20 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Spread 1 can crescent roll dough in 9 x 13-inch baker.
Place pepperoni in next, then sprinkle Cheddar, then Mozzarella and pour sauce over all.
Layer second rolls on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk in a large bowl until thick.
Add sour cream and 1 carton Cool Whip.
Mix until blended.
Layer bananas, cookies and half the pudding. Repeat layers.
Top with second carton of Cool Whip and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Mix all ingredients in large mixer bowl; set aside.
Mix salad dressing, mustard and salt and pepper together.
Pour over other ingredients and mix well.

title: reuben sauerkraut spread
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve on crackers or party rye bread.
Can also be mixed and put in crock-pot.

title: strawberry glace pie(serves 6)
directions: Bake and cook pie crust shell.
Wash and hull fresh strawberries.
Cut up 1 cup of berries.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup water gradually, until smooth.
Add cut up strawberries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup for garnish.
Pour in pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and berries.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.

title: seafood hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk.
Mixture will be thick.
Add onion and egg; beat.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Drop batter from spoon into hot deep fat.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown. Yields 3 dozen.

title: grandma's cake and pudding
directions: Mix cake according to instructions on box.
Save out 1 cup of batter.
Pour the rest of the batter in cake pan and bake until done.

title: hot tea toddy
directions: Combine water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon stick in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour mixture over tea bags in tea pot. Brew 4 minutes.
Remove tea bag.
Stir in juice.
Heat and serve in mugs with clove studded orange slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soak the yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and cool.
Beat the eggs until light.
Measure salt, sugar and shortening; stir into eggs.
Add scalded milk.
(Milk should be body temperature when dropped on wrist.)
Stir in yeast.
Add 1/2 flour, then continue to add flour until dough is stiff.
Knead about 5 minutes.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round or heart-shaped pans.
In a large bowl, combine all cake ingredients at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pans. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: calico salad
directions: Mix vegetables together (do not use frozen mixed vegetables that contain potatoes).

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender, stewed.
Remove from bone and put in deep dish or long casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Make a batter of flour and milk. Pour batter over chicken.
Add mixed vegetables to chicken.
Mix chicken or celery soup with broth from cooked chicken.
Pour over chicken, vegetables and batter.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
While simmering, make crust.

title: skyline chili(ala clark)
directions: Chop onions.
Put hamburger and water in a large pot first, then all the other ingredients at one time.
Simmer for 3 hours. Makes 2 quarts.
Serve over spaghetti.
Top with Cheddar cheese and oyster crackers.

title: easy egg custard pie
directions: Grease and flour (real thick) 9-inch deep pie pan.
Beat eggs, add
to
flour
and sugar.
Gradually add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour
into
pie pan and top with nutmeg.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean at 350°.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook all the preceding together except for carrots, until tender, then drain carrots and add to this mixture.
Bring everything back to a boil and pour in dish for serving.

title: orange roughy pasta florentine
directions: Coat a 2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Add garlic. Microwave on High 30 seconds; add cornstarch and next 3 ingredients.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 1/2 minutes or until slightly blended, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in spinach and fish. Cover with lid; microwave on High 4 minutes or until fish flakes. Let stand one minute.
Stir in cheese and serve over pasta.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup bran with boiling water; cool and add oil.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and buttermilk.
Add the dry ingredients.
Add 2 cups bran.
Bake at 400°.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Stir in flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick near the center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Spread Marshmallow Crme over cooled brownies.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate eggs and beat yellows real well.
Add can of Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well and beat in lemon juice until thick.
Pour into vanilla wafer pie crust.
Add meringue and brown lightly.

title: pickled squash relish
directions: Combine squash, peppers, onions and salt.
Cover with ice and water; soak 3 hours.
Pour off water and rinse.
Mix together vinegar, mustard seed, sugar and celery seed; heat until sugar dissolves.
Add squash, pepper and onions; boil 3 to 5 minutes. Seal in hot jars.
Great over beans and cornbread!

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef, onions and green peppers in oil.
Pour off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and bake covered in casserole at least 1 hour at 350°.
May add sliced or grated cheese on top when done.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and salt.
Set aside.
Blend margarine, sugar and vanilla; beat in egg.
Stir in flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool slightly, then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray 13 X 9 inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain; rinse with cool water. Let pasta dry on paper towels. For filling, in medium bowl, stir together 3 c. mozzarella with the ricotta and fresh basil. Using a teaspoon, carefully stuff pasta shells with prepared cheese mixture. Spoon 2 c. spaghetti sauce into prepared baking dish. Arrange stuffed pasta over sauce. Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over top of pasta. Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella. Bake manicotti for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with the Parmesan; bake for 10 minutes longer. Serve immediately.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles 4 minutes.
Leave cream cheese and margarine out of the refrigerator for 2 hours.
After they are softened, put the cream cheese and margarine in the microwave to further soften. Whisk them together.
Beat the 4 eggs with milk.
Mix all the ingredients together including the noodles.
Put all into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a bowl.
Mix last three ingredients in a separate bowl. Combine and chill 2 to 4 hours. Drain and serve with chips.

title: penuche
directions: Blend together sugar, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, or until sugar is dissolved.
Stir well.
Microwave 12 to 15 minutes on High or until small amount dropped in very cold water forms a soft ball.
Cool to lukewarm.
Using wooden spoon, beat vigorously until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Continue beating until candy is thick and difficult to work. Spread evenly in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and flour.	Mix margarine and cocoa and add to
mixture.
Add
nuts
and
vanilla.	Spread	in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread small
marshmallows
over top.
Return to shut-off oven to puff up	and
spread marshmallows.
Cool slightly and frost.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs and margarine thoroughly in 9-inch pan. Press firmly and evenly over bottom and sides of pan.
Chill. Beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Top with chilled cherry pie filling before serving.

title: reuben meat loaf(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse, drain and coarsely chop sauerkraut.
Crumble ground beef.
In a large bowl, place sauerkraut, ground beef, bread crumbs, corned beef, egg, parsley and garlic;
mix until well blended.
Pat one-half of the mixture into a shallow 1 1/2-quart round baking dish, forming a slight rim along outer edge of dish.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray large cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Rinse chicken in cold water.
Dip in yogurt, then in bread crumbs.
Bake for about 1 hour, turning once.
When turning, spray chicken with butter flavor Pam.

title: marshmallows(and you thought they'd always come in plastic bags!)
directions: Soak gelatine in 10 tablespoons water.
Heat sugar in another 10 tablespoons water until dissolved, add gelatine and let cool. Beat until almost stiff.
Pour into pans, thickly dusted with powdered sugar.
When stiff, cut in cubes and roll in powdered sugar.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together and add next 3 ingredients. Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening until mixture is like coarse cornmeal.
Beat egg slightly and add to wet ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients with dry and mix with a fork until blended.
It will be sticky. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours, then sprinkle pastry cloth with flour and roll out.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel peaches, cut up and discard seed.
Combine flour and sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Place fruit in 9-inch baking dish. Cover with sugar and flour mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Prepare Chili-O mix.
Add flour, shortening, tomato paste and water.
Mix well.
After browning tortilla shell, dip the whole shell into sauce, then fill as desired.
Roll like jelly roll. Leave seam on the bottom of pan.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Chop vegetables coarsely.
Heat large skillet or wok to medium-high setting, using bacon drippings or two teaspoons of vegetable oil.
Pour all vegetables into skillet or wok and cover. Cook 8 to 10 minutes only to heat vegetables and remove from heat while slightly crisp.
May top with crisp crumbled bacon.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain grease and set aside.
Place a layer of potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle some cooked sausage, diced onion and shredded American cheese over potatoes; repeat layers until all ingredients have been used.
Mix soup with 1/2 cup of water in bowl.
Pour this over casserole.
Slice 1/2 stick butter into pats and place on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: campbell's golden divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare stuffing as directed.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle turkey or chicken over stuffing.
Sprinkle onions, mushrooms and broccoli over chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Spoon soup (undiluted) over all.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.
Enjoy.

title: pizza
directions: Toast English muffins (each muffin will make 2 pizzas). Spread spaghetti or pizza sauce on top of toasted muffin (and/or meat).
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Place in oven until bubbly.

title: classic lasagne
directions: Saute onion and garlic in saucepan in 2 tablespoons of oil until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, 1/2 cup water, 1/2 teaspoon salt, herbs and red pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Combine beef, pork, parsley, eggs, bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Shape into 1/2-inch meatballs.
Saute in remaining oil until browned; add to sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: light carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
In a small mixing bowl, soak raisins in Port and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, sift together oat bran, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Place in another bowl the brown sugar, oil, milk, corn syrup, vanilla and egg substitute; mix with an electric beater for a minute or two.
Add carrots to the liquid mixture, then stir in the flour mixture, then the raisins and Port.
Pour mixture into prepared baking pan; bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick, when inserted in center of cake, comes out dry.
Let cool to room temperature, then cut into squares.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar and syrup.
Stir well and bring to boil.
Stir in condensed milk.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until it reaches 234° to 238° or soft ball.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir well.
Butter hands lightly and shape into balls.

title: joyce yawn's french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and margarine until tender but not brown.
Add flour, broth and water.
Simmer for 45 minutes covered.
Pour servings in soup bowls.
Top with sliced cheese (2 slices make it better).
Put a few croutons on top of cheese and place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla to eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients and nuts; add to egg mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: helen's golden wedding punches
directions: Serves 1 cup punch to 50 persons.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, oregano and parsley together.
Layer cabbage, meat mixture, sauerkraut and tomato juice.
Pour remaining ingredients over.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and let bake 15 minutes longer.

title: mom's soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, pepper and celery.
Put all ingredients in Dutch oven and simmer about 1 hour.

title: yam casserole
directions: Cook yams, drain.
Add canned yams (pour off some of the juices).
Mash all yams.
Add pineapple, orange juice and rum. Blend.
Pour into greased Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle with marshmallows. Bake at 400° until bubbly (20 to 25 minutes).

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Punch down. Turn out on lightly floured board.
Shape into rolls.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar in a small bowl.
Add flour and nuts; mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 3/4 cup for toppings. Press remainder into bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: asparagus and cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Add milk to make sauce.
Add cheese, pimentos and asparagus.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Server on toast.

title: soy-marinated flank steaks
directions: Poke the steak all over with the tines of a fork; cut in half against the grain to make 2 steaks. In a non-reactive bowl or large resealable plastic bag, combine the soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, oil, garlic, sugar and pepper to taste. Add the steak and turn to coat. Cover to reseal the

bag and marinate at room temperature for about 1 hour or refrigerate for up to 6 hours. Remove the steak from the marinade and pat dry with paper towels. Position the rack in the top position in the oven and preheat the broiler. Remove the steaks from the marinade and pat dry. Cook the steaks for 5 to 8 minutes on each side for rare to medium rare. Set aside on a cutting board for 5 minutes. Cut the steak against the grain, on an angle, into very thin slices. Arrange the slices on a warmed platter.

title: mothers roast beef and dumplings
directions: Place the beef roast in a large cooking vessel with salt, pepper and other seasonings; cover roast with cold water about two inches over top. Cook on medium high heat until roast is tender. Remove roast from boiling stock and let cool for several minutes. Slice or tear roast into strips. Place back into stock; bring to a boil and add prepared dumplings. Cook for about 15 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Drop by spoonful in hot grease or butter.
Use Teflon coated skillet when frying in butter.

title: homemade cocoa
directions: Mix ingredients together
slowly a little at a time.
Use lemonade scoop for 1 cup cocoa.
Add hot water.
Keep in airtight container.
Makes a large amount of cocoa.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken breasts and take off bones (save broth).
In a large bowl, put chicken (chopped), onion and bell pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: layered chicken and broccoli(microwave needed)
directions: Stir broccoli, onion, garlic, salt and pepper in a round baking dish, 8 x 1/2-inch.

Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) until vegetables are crisp-tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir. Arrange chicken and water chestnuts evenly on broccoli. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High (100%) for 3 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, 1 cup water and lemon rinds. Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil about 7 minutes.
Cool.
Add lemon juice and ice water.
Pour over ice in pitcher or tall glasses.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a plastic flowerpot.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Blend curry powder into Kraft mayonnaise.
Gradually blend in the evaporated milk.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Fill hot jars with apples leaving 1 inch headspace.

title: crisp
directions: Place fruit in bottom of glass dish.
Mix sugar and flour, then add egg.
Pour over fruit.
Pour margarine over everything. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayo, sour cream, water chestnuts, soup mix and spinach together.
Hollow out the bread and use it as a serving dish for the dip.
Use pieces of bread for dippers.

title: redi-cheese burger
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make burgers.
Bake in oven or fry. Serve on roll with alfalfa sprouts and a slice of red onion.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Remove chicken from the marinade and coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange on a shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear and chicken is tender.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place egg in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole; beat well with fork.
Stir in milk, sugar, corn, crackers and butter.
Cover; microwave at Medium-high for 10 minutes.
Stir well.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; microwave at Medium-high 5 to 6 minutes. When done, center will be just barely set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large crock-pot.
When this is completely combined, add 1 pound Velveeta cheese and let this completely melt.
Stir constantly.

title: lois' chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oats in blender to a fine powder.
In bowl with mixer, cream butter and both sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine oatmeal powder, flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add oat mixture to butter mixture; beat until just blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces, grated chocolate and nuts.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix all together about 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased muffin tin.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown at 450°.
Makes 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, jalapeno pepper and pimento in butter.
Mix cooked rice and corn to the sauteed mix.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Place in a buttered dish.
Cook for 20 minutes at 300°.
Grate cheese on top the last 5 minutes or until melted. (Can be frozen.
Leave cheese off until ready to cook.)

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sorghum, sugar, butter and water until it forms crystal ball when dropped in cold water, then add 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Make balls or leave loose.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-1/2 qt casserole dish.
Cover. Microwave 10-12 minutes on high.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes before serving.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into a well greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
In small mixing bowl, beat cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick near center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or drizzle with chocolate glaze.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Sift flour.
Cream together sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Mix in flour and flavoring, then beat in eggs one at a time until blended.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: soda cracker delight
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well; add vanilla.
Fold in soda crackers and chopped nuts.
Bake in 12 x 8-inch glass pan, well greased and floured, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dried fruit and coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Coarsely chop the dried fruit.
In a medium bowl, combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in the egg whites and vanilla.
Stir in the chopped fruit and walnuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 1-inch apart onto the cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until edges of the macaroons are golden.
Remove macaroons to cool. Repeat with remaining dough.

title: punch
directions: Mix all the juices together.
Add ginger ale and sherbet last.

title: sausage-cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish; set aside.
Brown sausage and onion in medium skillet; drain well.
Combine eggs, corn meal, corn, milk and oil. Pour half of corn meal mixture into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add soups and a dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over medium heat and then turn heat down and let flavors blend.
Serve on buns.

title: spicy hot refresher
directions: In covered blender or food processor, combine V-8 juice, cucumber, lime juice and chili powder.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes, one at a time, blending until ice is finely crushed. Serve immediately.

title: delicious pork roast
directions: Wash pork roast and pat dry.
Sprinkle pepper and paprika liberally over roast.
Place in 250° oven and cook until well done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Discard stems and break into small bite sizes (can be shredded). Combine with remaining ingredients.
Marinate 24 hours for extra good flavor or eat it immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: turkey apple salad
directions: In medium bowl, gently stir together turkey, apple, celery and raisins.
In cup, stir together dressing and brown sugar.
Pour over turkey mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 2 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Stir all ingredients (except apples) together with large spoon.
Add apples. Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rye boat
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, parsley, dill weed, sour cream and onion.
Make sure they are mixed well. Dice corned beef and combine with the previous mixture, making sure that the slices separate. Chill mixture overnight.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil; stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Don not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts, and bananas. Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9- inch cake pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes. Cool. Frost with cream cheese icing. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: dry orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not mix Jell-O with water; use dry.
Chill overnight.

title: rice lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium skillet, brown beef and onion; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce; mix well.
In small bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and egg whites; mix well.
In the prepared pan, spread 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 of rice and 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture; repeat layers.
Spread remaining sauce on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: quick and delish chicken soup
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add mushrooms and onions and cook 5 minutes.
Add broth, chicken and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in pasta, tomatoes, parsley and thyme.
Cook 5 minutes.
Yield: 9 cups.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix well with mixer; roll into balls and mash with a fork onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease 9 X 13 baking pan. In large bowl, mix first 5 dry ingredients. In a medium bowl, beat cheese, corn and chilies with their liquid. Stir in onion, eggs, milk and margarine until blended. Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moist. Spread batter in pan. Bake 30 minutes until golden brown and toothpick in center comes out clean. Makes 15 servings.

title: salisbury steak and onion gravy
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/3 cup of the soup with the beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties and brown; pour off fat.
Gradually blend in remaining ingredients, stirring to loosen browned meat bits.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain. Break into pieces. Beat eggs and add milk, salt and mustard. In greased baking dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese. Pour egg mixture over these layers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: brisket with rub
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Preheat oven to 250°. Apply rub to both sides of brisket (fatty side last).
Place in pan, fatty side up, and cover with heavy-duty foil or use roasting pan with lid.
Bake for 10 to 12 hours.
Can be cooked on grill.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Mix hamburger and dry soup mix.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drain vegetables and spread on top of hamburger mixture.
Mix together soups (do not add water).
Spoon or spread on top of vegetables, then place Tater Tots neatly atop of soup mixture.
Heat in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and heat thoroughly.
Good for large crowds.
Leftovers are even better.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until very smooth. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat just until yellow is all through the mixture. Add flour, one cup at a time, beating only until mixed after each cup. Add vanilla. Stir until stirred in.
Spoon into tube pan and cook at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute chopped onions and celery in butter.
Cook chopped broccoli in water.
Melt together cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine.
Add uncooked Minute rice.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chili corn taco
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil until tender.
Brown meat and drain.
Add celery and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serve as chili or spoon into taco shells or over chips.

title: crisp oven fried chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Dip chicken or fish in water, then in crumbs.
Put on nonstick sheet, sprayed with Pam.
If any crumbs remain, sprinkle on.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done. Makes 2 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix; spread in a 13 x 11-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: chili
directions: Slice sausage.
Brown sausage, ground beef and onion.
Lower the heat to simmer.
Drain the oil from meats.
Add remaining ingredients to meats.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Season to taste. Makes a big pot . . . enough to feed 12 hungry basketball players.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meats and cut in small pieces. Cool stock and remove grease. Cook bacon and brown onions in fat.
Cook 2 stalks celery with chicken or add 1 can cream of celery soup.
Cook corn in bacon drippings and let stand with creamed potatoes (add to stew last to prevent sticking).
Cook very slowly several hours. Season with salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Lightly brown. Add all other items and fry. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cabbage may be added halfway through cooking potatoes. Add 1/2 stick butter. Cover and complete cooking.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Stir in baking mix and nuts.
Mix until crumbly (reserve 1 cup).
Press mixture in pan and bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and sugar. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over mixture in pan. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: candy's chicken in wine sauce
directions: Flour and brown chicken.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Stir and heat in saucepan cooking wine, soy sauce and sugar.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or until sauce of barbecue consistency.
Turn chicken over at least once.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together hamburger, cracker crumbs and water.
Pat into a jelly roll pan (about 1-inch thick) and put into the refrigerator overnight to chill well.

title: turkey, swiss and mushroom crepes
directions: Lay turkey breast, skin up, on some sprigs of rosemary and oregano and bake in a covered dish with 1/2 cup water. Salt and pepper.
Cut turkey into 1/2-inch cubes.

Put approximately 3 tablespoons of turkey and 1 tablespoon grated Swiss cheese in the center of each crepe. Add 2 tablespoons of hot Mushroom Sauce. Roll up the crepe. Add 1 tablespoon Mushroom Sauce over the top of the crepe.
Garnish with rosemary sprigs.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Pour apples in buttered baking dish, 8 x 8-inch.
Sprinkle jello over apples and pour water over apples and jello.
Next sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Can be served with ice cream.

title: praline sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add sweet potatoes; cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until golden brown. Turn potato slices over. Reduce heat; cover and cook 5 more minutes. Remove potatoes from skillet. Add apples; cook 5 minutes on each side or until tender and golden brown. Return potatoes to skillet. Add sugars, pecans, cinnamon and salt, tossing to coat. Add 2 tablespoons water, stirring to mix. Cook 5 minutes, until potatoes and apples are glazed and tender.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add soups, enchilada sauce, green chilies and picante sauce. Cook until hot.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: lemon-pepper potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine Butter Buds, onion tops and lemon-pepper seasoning. Stir in water.
Add the potatoes.
Toss to coat well. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until potatoes are tender and beginning to brown, stirring twice. Goes great with Tangy Baked Chicken and has no fat.
Makes 4 side dish servings.

title: rich shortcake biscuits
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (flour through salt).
Cut in margarine.
Combine egg and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Knead gently on floured surface a few times.
Pat out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and bake on ungreased sheet 10 minutes at 450°.
Add pecans and raisins (English style).

title: kalua pig(hawaiian-style luau pork)
directions: Pierce pork all over with a carving fork. Rub salt, then liquid smoke over meat. Place roast in a crock-pot slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 16 to 20 hours, turning once during cooking time. Remove meat from slow cooker and shred, adding drippings as needed to moisten.

title: cooked finger paint
directions: Mix salt and flour; add cold water gradually and beat mixture with egg beater until smooth.
Add hot water and boil until mixture loses chalky appearance.
Beat until smooth.
Color with food coloring.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large bowl, beat softened cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk and beat until fluffy.
Add lime juice and green food coloring.
Mix until creamy and smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip; mix well.

title: mini kisses
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour two cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Slowly add the 2/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Beat until smooth and shiny.
Stir in with a spoon 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1 cup of nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 275° (or can turn off oven and leave kisses in oven overnight).
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: 24-hour cole slaw
directions: Place the cabbage and onion in a large bowl; set aside. Combine the vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and mustard and bring to a boil. Set off heat and add 1 cup oil. Bring to a second boil and pour over cabbage and onion. Let set for 24 hours. Stir before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Stir in oil and remaining ingredients. Batter will be stiff. Add apples last. Pour into a 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash the figs by filling a bowl large enough to submerge them in water.
Dissolve the salt and baking soda in the water.
Using your hands, toss gently so as not to bruise the figs.
Drain the water, rinse in clear water and drain again.
Put the figs and sugar in a large pot over medium-low heat.
Stir gently as they begin to cook.
Raise the heat to medium when syrup forms and let it come to a gentle boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 3 hours or until a foam appears around the edges of the pot.
Stir occasionally.

Spoon the hot mixture into 5 hot sterilized pint-sized preserving jars, filling to within 1/2-inch of the top. With a clean damp towel, wipe the rim and fit with a hot lid. Tightly screw on a metal ring.
Process in a hot-water bath for 15 minutes.
Using tongs, remove the jars.
Place on a towel and let cool.
Test the seals.
Tighten the rings.
Store in a cool, dark place.
Let age for at least 2 weeks before using.
Yield:
5 pints.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in water, salted to taste, until tender.
Cool; remove from bone and chop fine.
Combine chicken, celery, eggs, pickle relish and broth.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Chill.
Can be served on lettuce.
Makes good sandwiches.

title: fresh apple cake #3
directions: Blend sugar and eggs; add vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered fiesta spread
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion and beef until onion is tender and beef is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in chili powder, then refried beans.
Cook, covered, until heated through. Stir.
Spread avocado dip over mixture.
Top with shredded cheese. Heat until cheese is soft.
Before serving, dollop sour cream over cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: hot johnny tomato catsup
directions: *If you like it mild, leave out cayenne pepper.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Mix the chicken, mushroom soup, gravy, pimento, onion and water chestnuts together.
Cut crusts from bread.
Spread mixture on 10 slices of bread and cover with the other 10 slices.
Wrap individual sandwiches in plastic wrap or wax paper and freeze.
At serving time, dip the sandwiches, still frozen, in a mixture of beaten eggs and milk.
Coat with crushed potato chips and place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 sandwiches.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise, bouillon cubes, skim milk, flour and curry powder in a saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat until it thickens.
Pour this sauce over the broccoli and chicken.
Next, add a layer of cheese.
Melt the butter and pour it over the bread crumbs.
Put this on top as the last layer.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated steak
directions: Combine dressing, garlic, onion and a dash of salt and pepper in a shallow glass dish. Add steak, turn to coat with marinade. Refrigerate for several hours, turning steak occasionally. Just before serving preheat broiler or grill. Drain steak, broil or grill.

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Mix cinnamon with apple pie filling after mashing pie filling with a potato masher.
Spoon pie filling evenly down centers of tortillas.
Roll up and place seam down in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bring butter, sugar, and water to a boil and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over enchiladas and let stand for 30 minutes. Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.

title: honey wings
directions: Wash chicken wings.
Season with salt, pepper and Cajun seasoning.
Heat oven to 300°.
Place chicken wings in a roasting pan with 1/2 cup water, 1/2 stick of butter and 1/2 onion.
Let chicken wings bake about 30 minutes.
In a bowl, mix honey, red pepper and hot sauce.
Take chicken wings out and brush on honey mix and let cook for another 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple and save 2 cups pineapple juice. Cook package of vanilla pudding using 2 cups pineapple juice and 1 cup water.
Cook until thick.
Pour over fruit.
Chill.
When ready to serve, slice 2 to 3 bananas.
Mix and serve.

title: bran refrigerator muffins
directions: *If Raisin Bran is not used.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, approximately 5 minutes.
In a mixing bowl combine all ingredients, placing the bread crumbs on top.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Excellent casserole!

title: rice with green peas(servings:  8)
directions: Knead and rinse the rice.
Place the rice and water in a heavy medium size saucepan and leave it for half an hour.
Add salt and sake.
Place the saucepan with a tight fitting lid on low heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Keep it covered until done.
Heat over high heat for 9 to 10 minutes.
Then for 5 to 6 minutes over medium heat. Continue cooking over low heat for another 5 to 6 minutes. Finally, increase heat to high and cook only for 20 seconds.
Stop the fire and mix the prepared peas very quickly.
Cover rice with a paper towel, replacing the lid immediately.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Do not lift lid while rice is cooking.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar and eggs; mix well. There may be small lumps of cream cheese, that's okay.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate coffee cake
directions: Bake cake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese kolacky
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add milk, sugar and egg yolk. Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Chill dough.
Knead and roll out to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Using a small cookie cutter, cut out shapes and fill with fruit filling.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: chili powder substitute
directions: Blend in blender.
Use as you would chili powder.
Also excellent in baked beans.

title: mexican melt
directions: Melt cheeses (with salsa) with ground beef. Serve with Doritos.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beating water, egg, and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill for about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 - 9 minutes.
Place Hershey kiss in center of cookie while still warm.

title: maui-maui punch
directions: This was served at Chattanooga Louawa at So.
E. Conference. Serves 75 to 100.
Very good.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: On top of stove, cover ribs with cold water.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place in roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Pour off fat.
Add pineapple chunks and peppers.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: octopus bubbles
directions: Stir pineapple juice into club soda.
Drink!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Use desired cookie press. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: simple strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Combine flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, sugar, gelatin and buttermilk; mix until well blended.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Fold berries into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Cool 5 minutes, turn out of pans onto rack and cool completely.
Frost with Buttercream Icing.

title: homemade cream soup mix(lo-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in jar in cool, dry place. To make "legal" cream soup to equal 1 can condensed soup, combine 1/2 cup mix with 1 1/4 cups water or defatted broth. Cook until thick.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Flake crabmeat and mix it into the cream cheese.
Fill mushroom caps with the crab mixture and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Great appetizers for parties.

title: southern plantation salad
directions: Sprinkle shrimp with the lemon juice and set aside.
Combine other ingredients and stir in shrimp.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions,
celery
and
parsley in butter.	Put raw rice and
vegetables in a large casserole.
Mix together.
Add chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Blend salad dressing and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Sift and measure flour and sift with cocoa and soda.
Stir into salad dressing mixture.
Add boiling water and stir until smooth.
Add vanilla, pour into well greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: oven roasted "fries"
directions: Peel and cut potatoes as if making fried potatoes.

title: chicken fajita casserole
directions: Cut chicken into strips and cook in olive oil.
Add peppers and onions to chicken.
Add taco seasoning.
Cook until chicken is done.
Place chicken in casserole dish and add peppers and onions on top.
Pour salsa over this and add cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with sour cream.

title: boy scout biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix together first 3 ingredients. Combine shortening and milk and stir slowly, a little at a time, into flour mixture.
Shape biscuits and place in a greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix ingredients (except pie crust and cheese ) together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add layer of cheese slices over hamburger mixture.
Cover with your favorite pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Let start to gel and all 1 cup sour cream and onion and cucumber.
Mix well and gel until solid.

title: vanilla ice cream(custard)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Beat eggs into milk.
Slowly add to flour mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. When cooled, add half and half and vanilla.
Pour into freezer container and finish filling with milk.
(I usually cook the custard the day before and refrigerate overnight.)
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: curried rice
directions: Saute
onion in butter in a saucepan until tender.
Add water and
bouillon cube; bring to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Allow
mixture
to
return
to a boil; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour dressing over chicken. Place chicken in oven.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: wedding crab dip
directions: Blend all together.
Fold in crab.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup Gruyere and heat until bubbly in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 1 quart.
Serve with Melba toast.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a
large pot or kettle.
Remove. Saute onions, celery and potatoes.
Add water and seasonings. Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Combine flour with milk.
Add to kettle and cook until thickened.
Add corn, cream, cheese and bacon.
Stir very frequently.
Serve when cheese is melted and soup
is hot!

title: chicken cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 3-quart baking dish, place chicken. Top with cheese. Stir soup and spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices.
Mix margarine and stuffing.
Sprinkle over tomato slices. Bake for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter.
Mix soup and rice.
Pour into baking dish.
Add breasts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pecan filling and frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, almost 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until cool and spread between layers, top and sides of cake.

title: refried beans
directions: In iron skillet, heat bacon grease and add pinto beans.
Mash with potato masher.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and onion salt and stir over medium heat until beans are smooth.
Top with grated cheese.

title: third graders' favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and beat until light. Add egg.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture. Refrigerate for approximately 15 minutes.
Roll thin on board sprinkled with confectioners sugar (or flour).
Cut with your favorite cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Decorate with colored sugar.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; skin, bone and cut in cubes.
Mix chicken with other ingredients except stuffing mix.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle stuffing mix and dot with margarine on top. Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: tuna mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; set aside.
Combine tomato soup and cream cheese in medium saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until well blended.
Cool; add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold.
Chill several hours until firm.
Serve with crackers or on greens as a salad.

title: walnut frosties and topping
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream 1 cup sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and egg.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
With thumb, make imprint in center of each cookie. Combine topping ingredients and fill each cookie with 1 teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: corned beef balls in celery sauce
directions: Flake corned beef with fork.
Add bread, onion, egg and potato; mix.
Shape into 12 balls and brown on all sides in hot butter in frypan.
Place in casserole dish.
Add hot water to celery soup and mix.
Pour over balls.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can be prepared the day before, adding soup when ready to cook.

title: turkey broccoli rice casserole
directions: Heat soups and Cheez Whiz in heavy saucepan.
Add broccoli and turkey.
Place cooked rice in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Cover with broccoli mixture.
Pour melted margarine over Ritz crumbs and toss to coat.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You could use ham or chicken instead of turkey.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add soup, green chilies, sauce and chopped onions.
Heat thoroughly.
Crumble 5 to 6 tortillas in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half of meat mixture. Crumble an additional 5 tortillas on meat mixture.
Top with remaining meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pan sugar biscuits
directions: Pull biscuits in halves or fourths.
Get grease or Crisco or oil hot, place in skillet.
Turn when golden brown on every side. Remove carefully.
Place on paper towel, then roll in sugar or powdered sugar until coated.
A great sweet and chewy snack.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured pan.
Top with 1/2 sugar mixture.
Repeat.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pina colada pie
directions: To prepare crust, mix crushed vanilla wafers, sugar, nutmeg and 1/2 cup coconut.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Mix in order given, adding ginger ale and sherbet when ready to serve.

title: cream cheese peanut bars(1993 national peanut festival grand prize winning recipe)
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Mix well.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup creamy peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over cake and top with peanuts.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until layer is done.
Cool for approximately 1 hour and cut into bars.
Yield: 15 bars.

title: dilled chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pickles, dill and apples.
Moisten with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with almonds, olives and cranberry cubes (if used).
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey-fruit syrup
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together pineapple juice, honey, cornstarch, and ground ginger.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Stir in fruit.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a large casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Cover and bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins. Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg. Serve warm.

title: purple cloud
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Blend briefly. Pour into serving glasses.
Serves 2.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Cut tomatoes in small pieces or grind (I put them through food chopper).
Bring to a boil in cold water 3 times, draining off water each time.
Add all other ingredients, except pineapple. Cook slowly about 3 hours or until done.
Add pineapple last 5 minutes.
Put into hot sterile jars and seal.
May process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given in a 12 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard and sugar; spread evenly over top of salad completely sealing to edges. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours. Garnish with parsley.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg, then add lemon extract and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: chili con carne or chili(for weight watchers)
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook beef in boiling salted water to cover until it loses its red color.
Drain; discard liquid.
Break up any large pieces of beef; set aside.
In same pot, combine the onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes, adding 3 to 4 tablespoons water if necessary to prevent vegetables from sticking.
Stir in chili powder, 3/4 teaspoon salt, oregano and bay leaves.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add beef, beans, tomatoes and juice.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring often.
Divide evenly among 12 bowls.
Serve each portion topped with extra onion, if desired.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Crust:
Combine graham crackers, soda crackers and butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: panned oysters
directions: Heat butter in heavy skillet.
Add oysters.
Saute until done. Serve over toast.
Pour remaining drawn butter over bread.
Great for New Year's breakfast.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with wet hands.
Form 16 balls.
Brown slowly in hot oil, shaking pan frequently to keep balls round. Blend paste with other ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles or spaghetti.

title: chicken livers wrapped in bacon(for parties)
directions: Cut chicken livers in about 3 or 4 pieces each. Stir in other ingredients, except bacon. Cover and put in refrigerator for about 1 hour. Cut bacon slices in half.

Wrap each piece of chicken liver with a piece of bacon; fasten with a toothpick. Place in a broiler pan or any bread pan that is deep enough to catch the grease while cooking. Bake in oven at about 350°. Bake until bacon is done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Combine flour and soda.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in egg whites, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash rice.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into balls.
Place in pressure cooker on rack and pour tomato soup and water over meatballs.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream with hands.
Roll into balls and flatten. Brush with egg white.
Bake at 400° to 425° until brown.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: victorian pink punch
directions: Mix the Bacardi mix and 7-Up in a large glass punch bowl. Place rounded spoonfuls of pink sherbet on top.
Serve chilled.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: In shakeable container, place all ingredients; shake.
Chill 1 hour.
Bring back to room temperature before serving.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into oiled frypan.
When golden brown, place in casserole and cover with gravy made from remainder of ingredients.
Simmer in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Soak beans overnight and cook in salt water until well done. Prepare hamburger by browning in skillet with salt and onions added.
Combine beans and hamburger in small roaster.
Add tomato juice, catsup, chili powder and a small handful of brown sugar to suit taste.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350-375° oven.

title: apricot bars
directions: In large bowl cream butter and sugar. Add egg. Mix well. In separate bowl combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Press 2/3 of dough into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Spread with preserves; crumble remaining dough over preserves. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack. Cut into squares. Yield: 36 bars.

title: baked pork chop moana
directions: Place chops in single layer in a shallow baking pan. Mix wine and soy sauce; pour over chops. Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or so turning 3 or 4 times. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, turning and basting occasionally.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Then put in oven and bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon sponge custard pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, egg yolks, lemon juice, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into 1st mixture.
Pour into crust-lined pie plate. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 35 more minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite fudge sauce
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa and flour together in a bowl.
Boil the water and pour over the cocoa mixture.
Add the margarine, salt and vanilla.
Stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir, then microwave 1 minute longer.

title: pecan bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with crackers, leaving whole.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Mix sugar, margarine and butter together; bring to a boil.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Drizzle over crackers and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Wait 2 minutes and cut into bars.
Place on paper towel to drain some of butter.
Store in container.

title: homemade egg substitute(cholesterol free)
directions: Beat egg whites lightly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
Makes 6 tablespoons, equivalent to 2 whole eggs or 1/2 egg substitute.

title: campfire cobbler
directions: Put peaches in Dutch oven.
Mix in red hots.
Spread cake mix on top, but do not stir in.
Cover and bake right on hot coals 30 minutes.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and cornstarch.
Add milk, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and eggs.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Add coconut and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Cool.

title: scampi style shrimp
directions: In large skillet, stir the green onions and garlic with margarine and oil for 1 minute.
Add shrimp; cook and stir until shrimp are pink.
Add ReaLemon and salt and heat thoroughly. Garnish as desired.

title: mamma's pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; hold back whites.
Cream the sugar, butter and eggs; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together. Add alternately flour and buttermilk.
Add flavorings.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy meat roll
directions: Combine hamburger, egg, green pepper and onion.
Generously add salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread mixture onto long piece of waxed paper.
Pat meat mixture into a thin, long rectangle.
Spread tomato sauce over entire meat mixture. Sprinkle with helpings of cheese of your taste.
Neatly take wax paper and begin to roll rectangle into a rolled tube.
Place into a long dish.

title: peanut puffs
directions: Cream shortening with peanut butter and salt until light and fluffy.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Blend in vanilla, then flour.
Stir in peanuts; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Roll in sifted powdered sugar immediately after removing from oven.
When cool, roll again in powdered sugar. Makes 4 dozen.

title: merilee's chicken and rice salad
directions: Marinate chicken for at least 1 hour in salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt.
Mix together in bowl grapes, celery, pineapple, mandarin oranges, almonds, rice and mayonnaise; add marinated chicken mixture and mix together well.
Chill for several hours.

title: lazarus cheesecake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust and press into spring-form pan. Spray with Pam.
Mix cream cheese and sugar for 3 to 5 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 30 minutes.
Bake in spring-form pan at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 20 minutes.
In bowl, mix together sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Pour on top of cooled cake and return to oven for 10 minutes.
You can omit topping and top with fruit.

title: ann's steak sauce romaine salad
directions: Mix in blender, alternating egg and oil.
Serve over romaine lettuce with black olives and artichoke hearts.

title: beau's chicken(great; low calorie, fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken breasts for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and spoon salsa over chicken and then put 1 slice cheese on each piece of chicken.
Return to oven and cook for 20 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: You will need Wilton hard candy molds.

title: parkay orange holiday cookies
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat margarine, sour cream, sugar, vanilla, orange extract and peel in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil or until sugar is dissolved. Add cranberries and simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the 2 packages Jell-O.
Cool, then add the remaining ingredients.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: Mix sugar, water and spices in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove spices; cool.
Add fruit juices.
Refrigerate until needed. Just before serving, add ginger ale to juices in punch bowl. Garnish with slices of orange and lemon, studded with whole cloves. May be doubled or tripled as needed.

title: refrigerator salad
directions: Put marshmallows in bowl and add milk.
Put in microwave for a few seconds until melted.
Put cream cheese and sour cream in mixer.
Add vanilla and
mix well.
Pour in marshmallow mix and fruit cocktail (drained).
Mix together.
Add 1/2 cups nuts, if desired.
Make the day before and let chill overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put potatoes on to boil.
Brown and drain beef; add soup.
When potatoes are tender, drain all water.
Add milk and butter; mash together.
Layer hamburger, soup, potatoes, then cheese.
Brown in oven.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: spanish chicken casserole(lower fat)
directions: Saute chopped onion in 3 tablespoons chicken broth over low heat.
Add 14 ounces chicken broth and sour cream; continue to simmer.
Add flour and cornstarch; mix with a wire beater to blend.
Stir in water chestnuts, green chiles and mushrooms.
Cut tortillas into fourths.
Line a large casserole dish, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, with part of the tortilla pieces.
Fold chicken into sauce.
Spoon chicken sauce over tortillas and sprinkle 1/2 of grated cheese on top.
Repeat layers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: 1. Prepare macaroni according to directions on the package.

title: *coconut pie*
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili casserole
directions: Place 2 cups broken chips in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish; spread half of soup over chips.
Spread chili and beans over soup and top with remaining soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining chips and bake 5 minutes longer. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut-nut topping
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: aunt chris' fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme and nuts. Mix until well blended. Pour into 8 x 8 foil pans lined with wax paper and let set to cool. Will take 2 pans. After cooled, cut into squares.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in half.
Put into baking dish.
Spread with sugar and margarine mixed together.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, soup, cheese, onions and milk together.
Mix well.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Save half of butter to mix with cornflakes or crackers for topping.
Pour into baking dish and top with crackers.
Spread over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: built-in relish burgers
directions: Brown meat and onion in salad oil until meat is crumbly.
Pour off excess oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buttered toasted buns.
Serves 10.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts on top of stove or in microwave until cooked through. Put in bottom of 9 x 12 baking dish.

title: blueberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; allow to cool.
Stir in pie filling and lemon juice.
Chill until partly set.
Spoon half of Jell-O mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sour cream and sugar; spread over Jell-O mixture.
Top with remaining Jell-O mixture. Chill before serving.

title: super southern gal biscuits
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Cut in the margarine or shortening until crumbly.
Add the milk; beat in the egg. Knead 5 to 10 times.
Roll 1-inch thick; cut for biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bayou gumbo
directions: Dredge chicken in flour (1/3 cup).
Brown in oil.
Remove. Add onion, zucchini and garlic and saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, okra, broth and water along with seasonings.
Allow to simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add rice, corn and chicken; simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, add olives and heat through.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Melt butter in a pan. Crush Oreo cookies. Spread cookies in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour butter over cookies.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Mix vanilla and chocolate pudding together with 3 cups milk until thick.
Set aside.
Mix together the powdered sugar, 1 cup Cool Whip and cream cheese. Spread over cookies.
Pour pudding mixture over cookies and cream cheese.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed walnuts on top, if wanted.
Chill until firm.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slightly brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Spread three cups of cabbage in bottom of an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread meat on top of cabbage.
Top with remaining cabbage. Combine soup and water, spoon over casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: onion butter
directions: Mix soup mix and margarine.

title: hay stacks
directions: Melt butterscotch.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: molasses cookies(chewy german cookie)
directions: In a saucepan, mix together the molasses, sugar, spices and water.
Bring to a boil and sustain for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add nuts and the flour, mixed with baking powder. Mix well.
Let stand until cold.
Divide dough and roll out on board or cloth with a rolling pin or pat by hand. Cut into diamond shapes and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 dozen.

title: potato gnocchi
directions: Boil potatoes until fork soft; cool.
Mash down very well. Place on floured board and mix with flour.
May require additional flour; add gradually.
Knead until smooth.
Roll into thin rolls and cut 1 to 1 1/2-inches long.
Press lightly with a fork. Freeze on waxed paper in layers.
When ready to heat, boil in salted, boiling water, a handful at a time.
Gnocchi are done when they float to top.
Don't overcook.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in thin slices.
Cut peppers in fine strips. Dissolve salt in ice water and pour over sliced rings.
Let stand for 3 hours, then drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric and whole cloves.
Bring to boil and then add drained rings.
Heat to boiling but do not boil.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Add cream, all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: almond ham roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham, stirring until blended. Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on each ham slice.
Roll up jellyroll fashion, starting at short end.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze up to 1 month.
Thaw at room temperature 1 hour before serving. Cut each roll into 3/4-inch slices.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: scotch pancakes(breakfast)
directions: Beat ingredients together until smooth.
Use one rounded tablespoonful per cake.
Makes 40 (2-inch) cakes.

title: popcorn cracker jacks
directions: Blend butter, honey and peanuts together in pan.
Heat until well blended.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Spread out on cookie sheet in a thin layer.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across grain into very thin strips.
In skillet over medium heat cook beef and garlic until beef is brown.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce. Heat to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except corned beef.
Place in baking dish and bake until vegetables are tender.
(Add 1/2 cup water if cooking in conventional oven.)
Cover with corned beef and return to oven until piping hot.
May be topped with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: crock pot beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in crock pot on high for 3 hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix
sugar
and butter.
Beat in eggs.	Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° one hour.

title: ginger chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce and 1/4 cup water in shallow baking dish; add chicken pieces, coating well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Drain marinade from chicken.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok; stir-fry chicken and onion until chicken is slightly browned.
Stir in vegetables, ginger and wine.
Cover and simmer 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Combine cornstarch and water in small bowl until smooth.
Gradually add to skillet, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over rice. Yields 6 servings.
Low fat!

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients for 3 or 4 minutes. Fold in package of frozen coconut and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare box cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool 5 minutes.
Punch holes in top of cake with fork.
Pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over cake.

title: mexi-corn pudding(no fat)
