directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Combine egg substitute and milk; add to corn mixture, stirring to combine.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Place dish in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour hot water into pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: down east casserole(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain.
Saute scallops in 4 tablespoons butter.
When almost cooked, add shrimp and cook until seafood is opaque.
Drain.
Save liquid.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth. Slowly add milk (some of seafood liquid could be substituted). Cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Add sherry.
Add scallops, shrimp, and sauce to noodles.

title: corn pudding (large)
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Spray dish with Pam so it will come out easy.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: brittany's pizza
directions: Split each piece of bread into 2 pieces.
Spread tomato sauce on 1 side of all slice.
Put the cheese on top.
Place on a microwave-safe plate.
Microwave for 20 to 40 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: cameo ranch soup
directions: Briefly saut onion and celery on medium heat (do not overcook).
Add Ro-Tel, chicken broth and Ranch mix.
Slowly bring to a medium boil.
Add the diced chicken and Velveeta.
Stir until Velveeta is melted.
Serves 16.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix all ingredients together, then add Hershey bar, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Use ungreased cookie sheet. Make golf ball size cookies placed 2-inches apart.
Should yield 112 cookies.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour about 1/2 of the nuts on the bottom.
Melt together in microwave, the peanut butter chips and margarine.
Add condensed milk and stir to smooth consistency. Fold in marshmallows and press mixture on top of nuts.
Press mixture down.
(It helps to wet hands under faucet) and top with rest of nuts.
Press nuts down firmly.
Let set and cut into bars of desired size.
The taste is similar to Salted Nut Roll candy bars.

title: appetizer quiche
directions: Mix Bisquick, 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese and onions. Mix milk and beaten egg together and then mix all together. Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread remaining Cheddar cheese on top. Crumble the bacon over the cheese. Make sure that the meat is generous. Pour the melted margarine over top and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Cut while warm. Serves 15 to 18.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda with pastry blender.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture until dough leaves sides of bowl. Dough will be soft and sticky.
Pour dough onto floured surface; roll into ball.
Knead lightly 25 to 30 times.
Sprinkle with flour if dough is too sticky.
Roll it 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with round cutter.
Bake at 400° on a greased cookie sheet for about 14 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen biscuits.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Prepare chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix saltine crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken into melted butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Bake uncovered at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: peppy
directions: Cook, drain and rinse pasta.
Drain and reserve all juices. Mix juice, sugar, eggs, salt and flour.
Heat until thick.
Cool. Refrigerate overnight.
Separate juice and pasta prior to refrigeration.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; one at a time with flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add apples, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over flour and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased sheet pan. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: terry's kale soup
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces and brown in olive oil.
Skin and slice sausages into bite size pieces and add to beef to brown. Then cover meat with water and add washed (peeled if necessary) and chopped vegetables and cook until everything is tender.
Then add drained kidney beans and cook for another 1/2 hour.

title: montana potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with margarine.
Salt and pepper in enough water to cover until tender.
Add flour to milk and add to potato mixture along with ham.
Cook until thick.
Serves 2.

title: greek beef stew(serves 6)
directions: Blanch onions in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain and peel. In a kettle melt the 1/2 stick of butter over moderate heat.
Add the beef, and toss to coat it with the butter.
Do not let it brown.

title: turkey and mashed potatoes
directions: To Prepare:
Remove neck and giblets from cavities, rinse turkey and wipe dry.
Rub body cavity lightly with salt, if roasting unstuffed.
Cook neck and giblets for broth, for flavoring dressing and for giblet gravy.

title: deep fried squid rings
directions: Dry rings thoroughly with paper towels.
Coat with flour, to which salt and pepper has been added.
Heat oil to 350° or until drop of water sizzles immediately when dropped in oil.
Plunge basket laden with 1 layer of squid into oil, which should bubble vigorously on contact.
If you don't have basket for deep frying, use large spoon or tongs to immerse squid in oil and to remove. Fry until coating turns brown, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot with lemon-garlic butter or cocktail sauce.

title: tuna dip
directions: Drain water from tuna.	Mix everything together.
Place in blender or food processor on high speed until all is well mixed and smooth.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: old southern date cake
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Add nut meats and vanilla last.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 1 hour.
Use loaf pan.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Place rice and milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a slight boil.
Cover over low heat.
After 1 hour, add sugar and vanilla. Raisins may be added, if desired, last 15 minutes of cooking. Stir often; cook until thick.
Careful, may scorch easily!

title: spicy grilled corn
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in mustard, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and lemon pepper.
Place each ear of corn on a 12 x 9-inch piece of heavy-duty foil.
Drizzle butter mixture over corn.
Fold edges of foil to seal pouch securely, leaving space for steam expansion.
Grill over medium hot coals, turning occasionally for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco salad
directions: *One bottle is probably enough, but some people might like more; mix in.

title: tami's best cheesecake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese and add other ingredients in order listed, one at a time.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° at 1 1/2 hours or until set.
Chill and garnish with fruit.

title: tuna waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple with lemon juice.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: seafoam cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and beat for 1 minute.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for about 30 minutes or until browned.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate oatmeal pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until creamy and pale yellow in color, about 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Stir in coconut, oats and chocolate. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until nutty brown. Cool on rack; refrigerate to chill before serving.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick and smooth. Pour in container and store in refrigerator.
Serve on fresh salad greens.

title: swedish heirlooms
directions: Cream the ingredients and add nuts.
Roll into balls and flatten.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in 10x sugar while warm.

title: garlic grits
directions: Beat eggs; add milk to total one cup.
Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick and easy stir fry rice for 4
directions: Begin cooking rice. Follow directions on package for 2 servings. While rice is cooking chop onion into 1/2 inch cubes or small strips. Chop garlic. Place oil, onion and garlic into skillet on medium low heat. Let warm gently until onion begins to become translucent. Meanwhile, chop carrot into 1/4 inch cubes, (slice 1/4 inch long ways, lay flat, then long ways again, then into cubes) and set aside. Take one cup frozen green peas out of bag, cover with hot water and let set. Check rice and set aside when done. Turn heat up on skillet to medium high. When temp. is reached, add rice to oil, onion, and garlic and spread in skillet. Pour in soy sauce, wine and pepper. Let temp. rise back to medium high while turning with flat spatula. In center of skillet, separate a hole in rice. Put eggs in center (yellows still whole). As eggs are cooking, chop with spatula, cutting yellows and whites, stirring only slightly (the eggs will be chunky). Gently mix eggs with rice, maintaining egg chunks. Rice and egg mixture should be semi-moist and begin sticking a little to skillet. Turn mixture with spatula (eggs should be cooking quickly). Turn heat off and let eggs complete cooking, turning as needed. Drain water from peas and pour peas in skillet. Add carrots and turn with spatula to mix all ingredients.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll the biscuits in a mixture of the 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and place in Bundt or loaf pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix the 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 cup sugar and margarine together over heat until margarine melts and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn over onto platter.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: gourmet cheese balls
directions: Cut the cheese into bite size pieces.
Spread the flour on a square of waxed paper.
Beat the egg with a fork and mix well with the milk in a shallow bowl.
Spread the breadcrumbs on another square of waxed paper.
Heat oil in a deep fat fryer or wok to 325°.
Dip the pieces of cheese in flour, shaking off excess.
Dip in the egg and milk mixture and roll in breadcrumbs.
Deep fry for 10 to 15 seconds or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes approximately 30 pieces.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream until most of the lumps are gone. Add spices and mix in well.
Now top mixture with grated Cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes and sliced black olives. Chill for about 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: low-fat breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown sausage in skillet. When it's partially done, add onion, green chili and bell pepper. Continue cooking until sausage is nicely browned. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place bread in pan. Pour sausage mixture over bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Beat milk, eggs and mustard together and pour over cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Casserole may be made ahead of time and refrigerated. If so, set out at room temperature 15 minutes before baking.

title: rice krispies dessert
directions: Mix Rice Krispies and peanut butter.
Just bring to boil, syrup, sugar and vanilla.
In microwave, melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
In 13 x 9-inch buttered dish, pound down Rice Krispies mixture.
Spread chocolate mix on top.
Kids "love" this one.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; debone and put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all the soups and chicken broth together.
Drain the Veg-All and mix with the soup.
Pour this mixture over the chicken.
Mix the milk with 1 package of Bisquick and pour over the other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice into a bowl.
Stir in pudding and fold in Cool Whip, cherries, nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Place one crust in a pie plate as directed on package for a 2 crust pie.
Spoon in mixture. Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and oleo together and cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir ingredients until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Allow to cool and cut as desired.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Sift together in another bowl all dry ingredients.
To main mixture add alternately the sour cream and dry ingredients.
Mix very well.
Loosely fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Done when toothpick in center is clean.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix
all ingredients except milk with soup.
Make small patties and roll in flour.	Brown patties in skillet and place in baking
pan.
Pour	soup
and
milk
mixture
over	top
of patties.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german apple cake
directions: In large bowl, cream first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of ingredients to first 3 and hand mix well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° 40 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gravy for chicken or liver
directions: Heat fat from chicken or butter.
Add onions and celery and cook just a little.
Add flour, pepper and sage.
Cut up boiled egg and add.
Add meat of chicken or you can use liver.
Cook until thickens.

title: beef and onion cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator to firm up. Make into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Then add 3 cups crushed potato chips to chocolate.
Add pecans.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: coconut-butterscotch torte
directions: Crust:
Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Pat firmly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cut up in medium pieces.
Set aside. Reserve broth from chicken.
Put dry rice into a large, covered, heavy baking pan.
Add the soup to the broth and mix well.
Put cut up chicken on top of the dry rice.
Add all other ingredients and pour broth and soup mixture over the rice.
Bake for 1 hour or until rice and chicken is tender.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in blender; then slowly add vinegar. Blend thoroughly until creamy.
Last, add celery seed.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: simple supper beef and broccoli
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat cook beef or chicken and garlic until browned.
Add onion; cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Stir
in
soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling. Add broccoli.
Reduce
heat,
cover
and simmer until desired doneness of broccoli.
Serve over noodles.

title: cheese and bacon potato bake
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, heat broth to a boil; reduce heat.
Add potatoes and onion; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups broth.
In skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble bacon; pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings.
Blend flour into reserved drippings.
Gradually add reserved broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.
In greased 2-quart baking dish, layer 1/2 each potato-onion mixture, sauce and bacon.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, drain grease.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place monkey pot or 2-quart rind mold or Bundt pan on a pie pan to catch any excess drips.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Brush the inside of mold well with the butter or spray with vegetable spray.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients for 2 minutes on medium speed or until thick.
Add the Cool Whip. Mix until well blended.
Add the marshmallows.
Layer in bowl as follows:
layer of pudding mix, layer of vanilla wafers, layer of bananas.
Repeat until all pudding mixture is gone.
It's good to start with pudding mix and end with it on top. Sprinkle top with vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: white clam chowder
directions: Saute garlic and oil, pour clam juice in with garlic and oil, put cubed potatoes in and when almost cooked, put clams in and then parsley and milk.
Cook a few minutes longer.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients into well beaten eggs.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until comes done in middle.

title: double decker fudge
directions: 1. Line a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan with foil.
Place 1 cup peanut butter ships in medium bowl.
Set aside. in second medium bowl, blend 1/4 c butter,
cocoa and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 c peanut butter chips.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion with margarine for 10 minutes, stirring.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper, basil and oregano. Beat eggs with Muenster cheese.
Add zucchini mixture with eggs. Mix well and place in pie shell.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in 370° oven.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut delight
directions: Spray a large pan.
Place 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream in a bowl to soften.
Crush 2 sleeves of crackers.
Add sugar and stick of melted oleo.
Mix together and press in bottom of pan.
Mix softened ice cream with 1 cup milk and 3 boxes coconut cream instant pudding.
Spread over the crust - Freeze for 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and toasted coconut (optional).
May be refrozen.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sour cream.
Stir in sugar, 1 tablespoon of flour, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Stir in apples. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: malone supreme
directions: Barbecue chicken on grill; don't cook completely.
Chop chicken up into bite size pieces.
Cook noodles; combine chicken, celery, onion and soup.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese, followed by cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° just to heat through (approximately 30 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Line bottom of dish with white bread.
Brown sausage; drain.
Spoon sausage over bread; sprinkle with a lot of grated sharp cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour into baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple, pepper, onion, nuts and salt.
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Beat 1st three ingredients
well.
Blend others.
Place in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at
350° for 40 minutes in 9-inch deep pie shell.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/3 cup (3 heaping teaspoonfuls) and add 1 cup hot water.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Season the lobster pieces with salt, white pepper and paprika.
Melt 2 ounces of the butter in a saucepan.
Fry the lobster pieces gently about 2 minutes.
Add the brandy and the sherry.
Let simmer until liquid is reduced by half.
Add cream. Let simmer again until creamy.
Add remaining butter ( do not allow the lobster to boil while adding butter).
Rectify seasoning.
Serve over freshly made toast.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Cook on medium heat 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup salt and 2 tablespoons cream of tartar, adding 1 cup water, 1 tablespoon vegetable oil and food coloring.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes until mixture globs together and leaves sides of pan.
Stir constantly.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool cake.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in punch bowl.
Mix pudding with milk, as directed on box.
Spread 1/2 pudding on crumbled cake in bowl.
Drain pineapple and put 1/2 pineapple over mixture in bowl.
Spread 1 bag glaze on pineapple, begin with outside edge (needs to be touching sides of bowl to look pretty from outside).
Next layer, spread 1 cup Cool Whip.
Repeat layers beginning with cake.
Last layer, use rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and maraschino cherries, as desired.

title: curried celery soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, place celery, onion, carrot, potato, garlic, salt, curry powder and 1 cup of the chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Pour half of the vegetable mixture into blender and blend until smooth.
Remove and repeat with remaining vegetable mixture.
Return all the pureed vegetable mixture to the saucepan.
Add condensed skim milk and chicken broth to make desired consistency. Heat only until hot.
Do not boil.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Do not drain fruit.
Mix fruit and instant pudding. Fold in the Cool Whip and add the miniature marshmallows. Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs (or Egg Mates), pumpkin, salt, sugar, ginger, cinnamon and cloves together.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter substitute over mix.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares desired number of squares while still warm.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Thinly slice angel food cake.
Place on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place blueberry pie filling over cake.
Beat instant pudding with 3/4 cup milk.
Add and fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Place cream mixture over blueberries and refrigerate.
Always a hit!

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in lightly buttered baking dish.
Top with sliced cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill an 8 or 9-inch pan 3/4 full of sliced apples.
In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add the beaten egg and stir to form crumbs.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: mixed vegetables casserole
directions: Make a sauce by adding butter, flour and salt.
Add cheese and cook over slow heat until melted.
Pour
off liquid from can of vegetables and place in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over vegetables and bake 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour round pans (8-inch or 9-inch).
Drain peaches, saving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Prepare cake mix using the juice water mixture.
Bake and cool as directed.
Cut peaches into small pieces.
Mix yogurt, topping and peaches together.
Use as icing between layers of cake on on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put water in pot to boil.
Add dry mixture and stir until thick.
Place fresh strawberries in baked pie shell and pour in cooled mixture.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Combine all but last three ingredients for marinade.
Add meat.
Cover and refrigerate for about 36 hours.
Turn meat two times daily.

title: sausage and cheese delights
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and remove from pan.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Put meats back in pan and add cubed Velveeta cheese. Stir over low heat until cheese melts; add spices and stir again. Spread on party rye.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar. Combine dry ingredients, stir in vegetables and fruits.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 3 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each. Roll up, start at shortest side; roll to opposite side.
In medium saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour half of soup mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch pan (reserve remaining soup mixture for sauce).
Arrange filled crescents over hot soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining tablespoon of cheese.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve with remaining sauce.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix sour cream, soup and onion in a small bowl.
In another bowl, pour melted butter over dressing; mix well.
Alternate layers (2) of squash, soup and dressing in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: deluxe german potato salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
In the drippings, saute celery and onions until tender. Combine sugar and flour.
Add to skillet with vinegar, water, salt and mustard.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, carrots, parsley and bacon.
Pour the sauce over the potato mixture and stir gently to coat.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water for 20 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot; stir constantly.
Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas, carrots and pimento.
Spoon mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: hot corn bread(or mexican bread)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except peppers).
Chop peppers (with rubber gloves on) and add to mix.
Stir well and bake in well-greased pan at 350° for 1 hour or so.

title: broiled spareribs
directions: Broil spareribs in broiler oven until golden brown on both sides.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in large pan and boil for 10 minutes uncovered.
Place ribs in uncovered roaster pan and pour some of the sauce over them.
Bake in a hot 450° oven for 1 hour basting every 10 minutes with rest of sauce which should be kept boiling.
Serves 5.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in 1 cup of the apples.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in remaining 3 cups apples and nuts.
Place in large greased pan such as broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend onion, celery and bell pepper.
Saute in butter until clear.
Add crab meat, cream cheese, red pepper and salt.
Serve hot.

title: blackberry or peach wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, soda and salt until crumbly.
Mix water, eggs and vinegar together, then add to flour mixture.

title: corn ole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until squash is tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy hash browns
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 13x9 pan at 350 for 40-45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Cube the cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in 2-quart casserole.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large clear bowl, layer the first 7 ingredients in order listed.
Cover entire top of salad with mayo (amount used will depend on size of bowl).
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in order listed over mayo.
Cover salad and let set overnight in fridge.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook and stir bacon in Dutch oven.
Pour off all fat but 1 tablespoon.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in the fat until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except Parmesan.
Heat to boiling and simmer 15 minutes. Place small amount of soup at a time in blender and puree.
Reheat.
Serve with grated Parmesan on top.

title: double boiler frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and water in top of double boiler.
Beat at high speed 1 minute.
Place over boiling water; beat on high speed 7 minutes.
Remove pan from boiling water; add vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer on high speed.
Fills and frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or frosts a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: mary's nut muffins
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Do not beat.
Put in small muffin tins with liners.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: gratin potatoes
directions: Saute onions in margarine until soft and transparent.
In a baking dish, arrange in layers the sliced potatoes and onions. Sprinkle with garlic seasonings in between layers.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Add whipping cream all over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Increase temperature to 400°.
Bake another 10 to 20 minutes until potatoes are soft and brown on top.
Serve with broiled meat.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut and mix fruit, add nuts and 2 cups flour; mix well. Separate
eggs
and
beat
whites and yolks well.
Mix butter, sugar
and	both
parts
of egg together.
Mix 2 cups of flour into
this.
Add
cake
mixture and fruit mixture together and mix well.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add fruit, mixing well.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Spoon into pie crust and dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then peanut butter.
Mix and roll into balls to place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, catsup, water, brown sugar, celery, vinegar, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Serve on warm hamburger buns.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Line an
x	13-inch cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spray with vegetable oil spray.
Place 36 saltines side by side. Boil
sticks
butter
and
brown sugar for 3 minutes (watch clock).
Pour
mixture over saltines and bake 7 minutes at 350°. Remove
from
oven	immediately
and while hot, pour chocolate morsels
over and spread with a knife.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Cut or break into pieces.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles until tender. Put 3/4 of noodles on the bottom of a casserole dish. Layer chicken, peas and soup on top of noodles. Lay cheese slices on top of last layer. Put remaining noodles on top of cheese. Cover.

title: green beans oregano
directions: Drain beans.
Save 2 or 3 slices bacon for garnish and crumble remaining 4 or 5 slices.
In a large bowl, mix beans with crumbled bacon, condensed soup, mushrooms, soup mix and oregano.

title: sour cucumber pickles
directions: Pack washed cucumbers in jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Fill jar with vinegar until you can touch it with your finger.
Finish filling jar with water.
Seal jars.
Boil 10 minutes in cold pack canner.
Remove jars and cover with a cloth until cool.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients as usual.
Combine jello and water first. Use 12 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex pan.
Put half of strawberry mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Spread top with sour cream.
Spread remainder of jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with milk, juice and 2 tablespoons Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with 8 ounce container of Cool Whip and chill.

title: chicken-cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut each baked potato lengthwise into halves; scoop out centers, leaving 1/2-inch border.
Reserve pulp for another use.
Brush halves with 2 tablespoons of the butter. Arrange potatoes on cookie sheet and place in preheated oven. Bake until shells are hot, 5 to 7 minutes.
While potatoes are baking, cut chicken breasts in halves.
Flatten each half by pounding between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add chicken, herbs, salt and pepper.
Cook until chicken is golden, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the cheese into each potato half; top each with 1/4 of the chicken and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: scrabble mix(you'll never want to eat store bought chex mix again!!)
directions: Combine dry cereals, pretzels and nuts in large roasting pan. In small saucepan, slowly heat butter and bacon drippings until melted.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces and blend.
Pour over cereal mixture.
With a rubber spatula, gently stir ingredients to distribute the butter mixture.
In small dish, combine the seasonings and sprinkle over cereal mixture.
Again, stir gently to distribute all ingredients.
Toast in slow over 250 degrees for 1 hour.
During the hour, remove from oven every 15 minutes and stir.
Cool.
Store in tin canisters.

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients and add enough milk to make 1 gallon. Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix, form into loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about an hour.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add sugar, soda, butter, dates and nuts.
Pour boiling water over ingredients and let stand 5 minutes.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: sweet potato buried treasure puff
directions: Whip together sweet potatoes, pineapple, egg, butter, salt and cinnamon.
Swirl in cranberry sauce.
Spoon into greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry nut bread(my all time favorite)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Stir to mix. Set aside.
In another larger bowl, beat together eggs and oil. Stir in blueberries.
Stir in dry ingredients only until moistened (do not overmix).
Pour batter into 2 or 3 well-greased bread pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven approximately 50 minutes or until tests done with knife inserted in center that comes out clean.
Let cool.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes(quick and easy version)
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop dough about the size of a walnut onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press flat with the bottom of a glass that has been coated with sugar. (Dampen bottom of a glass so sugar will stick to it better.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, arrange broccoli. Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk together; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Immediately upon shredding raw potatoes, put in salted ice water; let stand 15 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and add sugar and milk.
Turn into a long baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with bits of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and Carnation milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy reaches 234°.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with walnuts.
Press into fudge.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Cream the shortening and peanut butter together, gradually beating in the sugar, egg, vanilla and milk.
Add the dry ingredients that have been mixed together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Indent the center of each cookie with your thumb.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. When cookies come out of the oven, place a Kiss in the center of each cookie.

title: original johnny's dock seasoning salt
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in a large bowl and set aside. Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in sauce pan.
Cook until thickened, remove from heat, stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Pour over berries, mix well. Pour into pie shell, refrigerate until set.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir in flour which has been sifted with soda.
Mix well. Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Roll out and cut or shape as desired. Allow to rise until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 24 rolls.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake and bake, following directions on package.
Let cake cool.
Add 1 cup of hot water to jello to dissolve.
Poke holes in cake; pour dissolved jello over cake.
Let set in icebox one hour.
Top with whipped topping.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/3 cup melted margarine, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, soup and cheese.
Put in large casserole dish.
Mix 1/3 cup melted margarine and dressing mix; pour on top evenly. Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes or until golden on top.

title: easter basket cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake per package directions for original recipe.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Spread with frosting; top with 2nd cake layer and frost.
Frost outer layers.

title: rouladen(a beautiful make ahead for a buffet; i serve this at christmas.)
directions: Have meat cutter cut roast (across grain) into wafer thin slices.
Put meat and Italian dressing in Ziploc bag.
Marinate overnight, turning several times.
Remove meat; discard marinade. Flatten each slice of beef and place several pieces of carrot and celery on beef.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place in Ziploc bag containing about 1/3 cup flour; shake to coat meat evenly.
Put sausage and meat roll-ups in a 300° electric frypan or large Dutch oven.
Brown all meat, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with noodles or potatoes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add pepperoni, mushrooms and sauce; set aside.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef, stirring until crumbly.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in pepperoni, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
